2285LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2286 Expression* location) {
2287 switch (location->kind) {
2288 case AstNode::Kind::kIdentifierExpression:
2289 return GetLocationReference(static_cast<IdentifierExpression*>(location));
2290 case AstNode::Kind::kFieldAccessExpression:
2291 return GetLocationReference(
2292 static_cast<FieldAccessExpression*>(location));
2293 case AstNode::Kind::kElementAccessExpression:
2294 return GetLocationReference(
2295 static_cast<ElementAccessExpression*>(location));
2296 case AstNode::Kind::kDereferenceExpression:
2297 return GetLocationReference(
2298 static_cast<DereferenceExpression*>(location));
2299 default:
2300 return LocationReference::Temporary(Visit(location), "expression");
2301 }
2302}

2309
2310LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFieldAccess(
2311 LocationReference reference, const std::string& fieldname,
2312 bool ignore_stuct_field_constness, std::optional<SourcePosition> pos) {
2313 if (reference.IsVariableAccess() &&
2314 reference.variable().type()->StructSupertype()) {
2315 const StructType* type = *reference.variable().type()->StructSupertype();
2316 const Field& field = type->LookupField(fieldname);
2317 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2318 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(*pos, field.pos);
2319 }
2320 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2321 KytheData::AddClassFieldUse(*pos, &field);
2322 }
2323 if (field.const_qualified) {
2324 VisitResult t_value = ProjectStructField(reference.variable(), fieldname);
2325 return LocationReference::Temporary(
2326 t_value, "for constant field '" + field.name_and_type.name + "'");
2327 } else {
2328 return LocationReference::VariableAccess(
2329 ProjectStructField(reference.variable(), fieldname));
2330 }
2331 }
2332 if (reference.IsTemporary() &&
2333 reference.temporary().type()->StructSupertype()) {
2334 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2335 const StructType* type = *reference.temporary().type()->StructSupertype();
2336 const Field& field = type->LookupField(fieldname);
2337 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(*pos, field.pos);
2338 }
2339 return LocationReference::Temporary(
2340 ProjectStructField(reference.temporary(), fieldname),
2341 reference.temporary_description());
2342 }
2343 if (std::optional<const Type*> referenced_type = reference.ReferencedType()) {
2344 if ((*referenced_type)->IsBitFieldStructType()) {
2345 const BitFieldStructType* bitfield_struct =
2346 BitFieldStructType::cast(*referenced_type);
2347 const BitField& field = bitfield_struct->LookupField(fieldname);
2348 return LocationReference::BitFieldAccess(reference, field);
2349 }
2350 if (const auto type_wrapped_in_smi = Type::MatchUnaryGeneric(
2351 (*referenced_type), TypeOracle::GetSmiTaggedGeneric())) {
2352 const BitFieldStructType* bitfield_struct =
2353 BitFieldStructType::DynamicCast(*type_wrapped_in_smi);
2354 if (bitfield_struct == nullptr) {
2355 ReportError(
2356 "When a value of type SmiTagged<T> is used in a field access "
2357 "expression, T is expected to be a bitfield struct type. Instead, "
2358 "T "
2359 "is ",
2360 **type_wrapped_in_smi);
2361 }
2362 const BitField& field = bitfield_struct->LookupField(fieldname);
2363 return LocationReference::BitFieldAccess(reference, field);
2364 }
2365 }
2366 if (reference.IsHeapReference()) {
2367 VisitResult ref = reference.heap_reference();
2368 bool is_const;
2369 auto generic_type =
2370 TypeOracle::MatchReferenceGeneric(ref.type(), &is_const);
2371 if (!generic_type) {
2372 ReportError(
2373 "Left-hand side of field access expression is marked as a reference "
2374 "but is not of type Reference<...>. Found type: ",
2375 ref.type()->ToString());
2376 }
2377 if (auto struct_type = (*generic_type)->StructSupertype()) {
2378 const Field& field = (*struct_type)->LookupField(fieldname);
2379 // Update the Reference's type to refer to the field type within the
2380 // struct.
2381 ref.SetType(TypeOracle::GetReferenceType(
2382 field.name_and_type.type,
2383 is_const ||
2384 (field.const_qualified && !ignore_stuct_field_constness)));
2385 if (!field.offset.has_value()) {
2386 Error("accessing field with unknown offset").Throw();
2387 }
2388 if (*field.offset != 0) {
2389 // Copy the Reference struct up the stack and update the new copy's
2390 // |offset| value to point to the struct field.
2391 StackScope scope(this);
2392 ref = GenerateCopy(ref);
2393 VisitResult ref_offset = ProjectStructField(ref, "offset");
2394 VisitResult struct_offset{
2395 TypeOracle::GetIntPtrType()->ConstexprVersion(),
2396 std::to_string(*field.offset)};
2397 VisitResult updated_offset =
2398 GenerateCall("+", Arguments{{ref_offset, struct_offset}, {}});
2399 assembler().Poke(ref_offset.stack_range(), updated_offset.stack_range(),
2400 ref_offset.type());
2401 ref = scope.Yield(ref);
2402 }
2403 return LocationReference::HeapReference(ref);
2404 }
2405 }
2406 VisitResult object_result = GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference);
2407 if (std::optional<const ClassType*> class_type =
2408 object_result.type()->ClassSupertype()) {
2409 // This is a hack to distinguish the situation where we want to use
2410 // overloaded field accessors from when we want to create a reference.
2411 bool has_explicit_overloads = TestLookupCallable(
2412 QualifiedName{"." + fieldname}, {object_result.type()});
2413 if ((*class_type)->HasField(fieldname) && !has_explicit_overloads) {
2414 const Field& field = (*class_type)->LookupField(fieldname);
2415 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data() && pos.has_value()) {
2416 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(*pos, field.pos);
2417 }
2418 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2419 KytheData::AddClassFieldUse(*pos, &field);
2420 }
2421 return GenerateFieldReference(object_result, field, *class_type);
2422 }
2423 }
2424 return LocationReference::FieldAccess(object_result, fieldname);
2425}

2427LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2428 ElementAccessExpression* expr) {
2429 LocationReference reference = GetLocationReference(expr->array);
2430 VisitResult index = Visit(expr->index);
2431 if (reference.IsHeapSlice()) {

2433 } else {

2438
2439LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GenerateReferenceToItemInHeapSlice(
2440 LocationReference slice, VisitResult index) {
2441 DCHECK(slice.IsHeapSlice());
2442 Arguments arguments{{index}, {}};
2443 const StructType* slice_type = *slice.heap_slice().type()->StructSupertype();
2444 Method* method = LookupMethod("AtIndex", slice_type, arguments, {});
2445 // The reference has to be treated like a normal value when calling methods
2446 // on the underlying slice implementation.
2447 LocationReference slice_value =
2448 LocationReference::Temporary(slice.GetVisitResult(), "slice as value");
2449 return LocationReference::HeapReference(
2450 GenerateCall(method, std::move(slice_value), arguments, {}, false));
2451}
2452
2453LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2454 IdentifierExpression* expr) {
2455 if (expr->namespace_qualification.empty()) {
2456 if (std::optional<Binding<LocalValue>*> value =
2457 TryLookupLocalValue(expr->name->value)) {
2458 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
2459 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->name->pos,
2460 (*value)->declaration_position());
2461 }
2462 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2463 if (!expr->IsThis()) {
2464 DCHECK_EQ(expr->name->pos.end.column - expr->name->pos.start.column,
2465 expr->name->value.length());
2466 KytheData::AddBindingUse(expr->name->pos, *value);
2467 }
2468 }
2469 if (!expr->generic_arguments.empty()) {
2470 ReportError("cannot have generic parameters on local name ",
2471 expr->name);
2472 }
2473 return (*value)->GetLocationReference(*value);
2474 }
2475 }
2476
2477 if (expr->IsThis()) {
2478 ReportError("\"this\" cannot be qualified");
2479 }
2480 QualifiedName name =
2481 QualifiedName(expr->namespace_qualification, expr->name->value);
2482 if (std::optional<Builtin*> builtin = Declarations::TryLookupBuiltin(name)) {
2483 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
2484 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->name->pos,
2485 (*builtin)->Position());
2486 }
2487 // TODO(v8:12261): Consider collecting KytheData here.
2488 return LocationReference::Temporary(GetBuiltinCode(*builtin),
2489 "builtin " + expr->name->value);
2490 }
2491 if (!expr->generic_arguments.empty()) {
2492 GenericCallable* generic = Declarations::LookupUniqueGeneric(name);
2493 Callable* specialization =
2494 GetOrCreateSpecialization(SpecializationKey<GenericCallable>{
2495 generic, TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->generic_arguments)});
2496 if (Builtin* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(specialization)) {
2497 DCHECK(!builtin->IsExternal());
2498 return LocationReference::Temporary(GetBuiltinCode(builtin),
2499 "builtin " + expr->name->value);
2500 } else {
2501 ReportError("cannot create function pointer for non-builtin ",
2502 generic->name());
2503 }
2504 }
2505 Value* value = Declarations::LookupValue(name);
2506 CHECK(value->Position().source.IsValid());
2507 if (auto stream = CurrentFileStreams::Get()) {
2508 stream->required_builtin_includes.insert(value->Position().source);
2509 }
2510 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
2511 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->name->pos, value->name()->pos);
2512 }
2513 if (auto* constant = NamespaceConstant::DynamicCast(value)) {
2514 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2515 KytheData::AddConstantUse(expr->name->pos, constant);
2516 }
2517 if (constant->type()->IsConstexpr()) {
2518 return LocationReference::Temporary(
2519 VisitResult(constant->type(), constant->external_name() + "(state_)"),
2520 "namespace constant " + expr->name->value);
2521 }
2522 assembler().Emit(NamespaceConstantInstruction{constant});
2523 StackRange stack_range =
2524 assembler().TopRange(LoweredSlotCount(constant->type()));
2525 return LocationReference::Temporary(
2526 VisitResult(constant->type(), stack_range),
2527 "namespace constant " + expr->name->value);
2528 }
2529 ExternConstant* constant = ExternConstant::cast(value);
2530 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
2531 KytheData::AddConstantUse(expr->name->pos, constant);
2532 }
2533 return LocationReference::Temporary(constant->value(),
2534 "extern value " + expr->name->value);
2535}
2536
2537LocationReference ImplementationVisitor::GetLocationReference(
2538 DereferenceExpression* expr) {
2539 VisitResult ref = Visit(expr->reference);
2540 if (!TypeOracle::MatchReferenceGeneric(ref.type())) {
2541 Error("Operator * expects a reference type but found a value of type ",
2542 *ref.type())
2543 .Throw();
2544 }
2545 return LocationReference::HeapReference(ref);
2546}
2547
2548VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateFetchFromLocation(
2549 const LocationReference& reference) {
2550 if (reference.IsTemporary()) {
2551 return GenerateCopy(reference.temporary());
2552 } else if (reference.IsVariableAccess()) {
2553 return GenerateCopy(reference.variable());
2554 } else if (reference.IsHeapReference()) {
2555 const Type* referenced_type = *reference.ReferencedType();
2556 if (referenced_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrHoleType()) {
2557 return GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
2558 "LoadFloat64OrHole"),
2559 Arguments{{reference.heap_reference()}, {}});
2560 } else if (auto struct_type = referenced_type->StructSupertype()) {
2561 StackRange result_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2562 for (const Field& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
2563 StackScope scope(this);
2564 const std::string& fieldname = field.name_and_type.name;
2565 VisitResult field_value = scope.Yield(GenerateFetchFromLocation(
2566 GenerateFieldAccess(reference, fieldname)));
2567 result_range.Extend(field_value.stack_range());
2568 }
2569 return VisitResult(referenced_type, result_range);
2570 } else {
2571 GenerateCopy(reference.heap_reference());
2572 FieldSynchronization sync = reference.heap_reference_synchronization();
2573 assembler().Emit(LoadReferenceInstruction{referenced_type, sync});
2574 DCHECK_EQ(1, LoweredSlotCount(referenced_type));
2575 return VisitResult(referenced_type, assembler().TopRange(1));
2576 }
2577 } else if (reference.IsBitFieldAccess()) {
2578 // First fetch the bitfield struct, then get the bits out of it.
2579 VisitResult bit_field_struct =
2580 GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference.bit_field_struct_location());
2581 assembler().Emit(LoadBitFieldInstruction{bit_field_struct.type(),
2582 reference.bit_field()});
2583 return VisitResult(*reference.ReferencedType(), assembler().TopRange(1));
2584 } else {
2585 if (reference.IsHeapSlice()) {
2586 ReportError(
2587 "fetching a value directly from an indexed field isn't allowed");
2588 }
2589 DCHECK(reference.IsCallAccess());
2590 return GenerateCall(reference.eval_function(),
2591 Arguments{reference.call_arguments(), {}});
2592 }
2593}
2594
2595void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateAssignToLocation(
2596 const LocationReference& reference, const VisitResult& assignment_value) {
2597 if (reference.IsCallAccess()) {
2598 Arguments arguments{reference.call_arguments(), {}};
2599 arguments.parameters.push_back(assignment_value);
2600 GenerateCall(reference.assign_function(), arguments);
2601 } else if (reference.IsVariableAccess()) {
2602 VisitResult variable = reference.variable();
2603 VisitResult converted_value =
2604 GenerateImplicitConvert(variable.type(), assignment_value);
2605 assembler().Poke(variable.stack_range(), converted_value.stack_range(),
2606 variable.type());
2607
2608 // Local variables are detected by the existence of a binding. Assignment
2609 // to local variables is recorded to support lint errors.
2610 if (reference.binding()) {
2611 (*reference.binding())->SetWritten();
2612 }
2613 } else if (reference.IsHeapSlice()) {
2614 ReportError("assigning a value directly to an indexed field isn't allowed");
2615 } else if (reference.IsHeapReference()) {
2616 const Type* referenced_type = *reference.ReferencedType();
2617 if (reference.IsConst()) {
2618 Error("cannot assign to const value of type ", *referenced_type).Throw();
2619 }
2620 if (referenced_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrHoleType()) {
2621 GenerateCall(
2622 QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
2623 "StoreFloat64OrHole"),
2624 Arguments{{reference.heap_reference(), assignment_value}, {}});
2625 } else if (auto struct_type = referenced_type->StructSupertype()) {
2626 if (!assignment_value.type()->IsSubtypeOf(referenced_type)) {
2627 ReportError("Cannot assign to ", *referenced_type,
2628 " with value of type ", *assignment_value.type());
2629 }
2630 for (const Field& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
2631 const std::string& fieldname = field.name_and_type.name;
2632 // Allow assignment of structs even if they contain const fields.
2633 // Const on struct fields just disallows direct writes to them.
2634 bool ignore_stuct_field_constness = true;
2635 GenerateAssignToLocation(
2636 GenerateFieldAccess(reference, fieldname,
2637 ignore_stuct_field_constness),
2638 ProjectStructField(assignment_value, fieldname));
2639 }
2640 } else {
2641 GenerateCopy(reference.heap_reference());
2642 VisitResult converted_assignment_value =
2643 GenerateImplicitConvert(referenced_type, assignment_value);
2644 if (referenced_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64Type()) {
2645 VisitResult silenced_float_value = GenerateCall(
2646 "Float64SilenceNaN", Arguments{{assignment_value}, {}});
2647 assembler().Poke(converted_assignment_value.stack_range(),
2648 silenced_float_value.stack_range(), referenced_type);
2649 }
2650 assembler().Emit(StoreReferenceInstruction{referenced_type});
2651 }
2652 } else if (reference.IsBitFieldAccess()) {
2653 // First fetch the bitfield struct, then set the updated bits, then store
2654 // it back to where we found it.
2655 VisitResult bit_field_struct =
2656 GenerateFetchFromLocation(reference.bit_field_struct_location());
2657 VisitResult converted_value =
2658 GenerateImplicitConvert(*reference.ReferencedType(), assignment_value);
2659 VisitResult updated_bit_field_struct =
2660 GenerateSetBitField(bit_field_struct.type(), reference.bit_field(),
2661 bit_field_struct, converted_value);
2662 GenerateAssignToLocation(reference.bit_field_struct_location(),
2663 updated_bit_field_struct);
2664 } else {
2665 DCHECK(reference.IsTemporary());
2666 ReportError("cannot assign to const-bound or temporary ",
2667 reference.temporary_description());
2668 }
2669}
2670
2671VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GeneratePointerCall(
2672 Expression* callee, const Arguments& arguments, bool is_tailcall) {
2673 StackScope scope(this);
2674 TypeVector parameter_types(arguments.parameters.ComputeTypeVector());
2675 VisitResult callee_result = Visit(callee);
2676 if (!callee_result.type()->IsBuiltinPointerType()) {
2677 std::stringstream stream;
2678 stream << "Expected a function pointer type but found "
2679 << *callee_result.type();
2680 ReportError(stream.str());
2681 }
2682 const BuiltinPointerType* type =
2683 BuiltinPointerType::cast(callee_result.type());
2684
2685 if (type->parameter_types().size() != parameter_types.size()) {
2686 std::stringstream stream;
2687 stream << "parameter count mismatch calling function pointer with Type: "
2688 << *type << " - expected "
2689 << std::to_string(type->parameter_types().size()) << ", found "
2690 << std::to_string(parameter_types.size());
2691 ReportError(stream.str());
2692 }
2693
2694 ParameterTypes types{type->parameter_types(), false};
2695 Signature sig;
2696 sig.parameter_types = types;
2697 if (!IsCompatibleSignature(sig, parameter_types, 0)) {
2698 std::stringstream stream;
2699 stream << "parameters do not match function pointer signature. Expected: ("
2700 << type->parameter_types() << ") but got: (" << parameter_types
2701 << ")";
2702 ReportError(stream.str());
2703 }
2704
2705 callee_result = GenerateCopy(callee_result);
2706 StackRange arg_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2707 for (size_t current = 0; current < arguments.parameters.size(); ++current) {
2708 const Type* to_type = type->parameter_types()[current];
2709 arg_range.Extend(
2710 GenerateImplicitConvert(to_type, arguments.parameters[current])
2711 .stack_range());
2712 }
2713
2714 assembler().Emit(
2715 CallBuiltinPointerInstruction{is_tailcall, type, arg_range.Size()});
2716
2717 if (is_tailcall) {
2718 return VisitResult::NeverResult();
2719 }
2720 DCHECK_EQ(1, LoweredSlotCount(type->return_type()));
2721 return scope.Yield(VisitResult(type->return_type(), assembler().TopRange(1)));
2722}
2723
2724void ImplementationVisitor::AddCallParameter(
2725 Callable* callable, VisitResult parameter, const Type* parameter_type,
2726 std::vector<VisitResult>* converted_arguments, StackRange* argument_range,
2727 std::vector<std::string>* constexpr_arguments, bool inline_macro) {
2728 VisitResult converted;
2729 if ((converted_arguments->size() < callable->signature().implicit_count) &&
2730 parameter.type()->IsTopType()) {
2731 converted = GenerateCopy(parameter);
2732 } else {
2733 converted = GenerateImplicitConvert(parameter_type, parameter);
2734 }
2735 converted_arguments->push_back(converted);
2736 if (!inline_macro) {
2737 if (converted.IsOnStack()) {
2738 argument_range->Extend(converted.stack_range());
2739 } else {
2740 constexpr_arguments->push_back(converted.constexpr_value());
2741 }
2742 }
2743}

2745namespace {
2746std::pair<std::string, std::string> GetClassInstanceTypeRange(
2747 const ClassType* class_type) {
2748 std::pair<std::string, std::string> result;
2749 if (class_type->InstanceTypeRange()) {
2750 auto instance_type_range = *class_type->InstanceTypeRange();
2751 std::string instance_type_string_first =
2752 "static_cast<InstanceType>(" +
2753 std::to_string(instance_type_range.first) + ")";
2754 std::string instance_type_string_second =
2755 "static_cast<InstanceType>(" +
2756 std::to_string(instance_type_range.second) + ")";
2757 result =
2758 std::make_pair(instance_type_string_first, instance_type_string_second);
2759 } else {
2760 ReportError(
2761 "%Min/MaxInstanceType must take a class type that is either a string "
2762 "or has a generated instance type range");
2763 }
2764 return result;
2765}
2766} // namespace
2767
2768VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCall(
2769 Callable* callable, std::optional<LocationReference> this_reference,
2770 Arguments arguments, const TypeVector& specialization_types,
2771 bool is_tailcall) {
2772 CHECK(callable->Position().source.IsValid());
2773 if (auto stream = CurrentFileStreams::Get()) {
2774 stream->required_builtin_includes.insert(callable->Position().source);
2775 }
2776
2777 const Type* return_type = callable->signature().return_type;
2778
2779 if (is_tailcall) {
2780 if (Builtin* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(CurrentCallable::Get())) {
2781 const Type* outer_return_type = builtin->signature().return_type;
2782 if (!return_type->IsSubtypeOf(outer_return_type)) {
2783 Error("Cannot tailcall, type of result is ", *return_type,
2784 " but should be a subtype of ", *outer_return_type, ".");
2785 }
2786 } else {
2787 Error("Tail calls are only allowed from builtins");
2788 }
2789 }
2790
2791 bool inline_macro = callable->ShouldBeInlined(output_type_);
2792 std::vector<VisitResult> implicit_arguments;
2793 for (size_t i = 0; i < callable->signature().implicit_count; ++i) {
2794 std::string implicit_name = callable->signature().parameter_names[i]->value;
2795 std::optional<Binding<LocalValue>*> val =
2796 TryLookupLocalValue(implicit_name);
2797 if (val) {
2798 implicit_arguments.push_back(
2799 GenerateFetchFromLocation((*val)->GetLocationReference(*val)));
2800 } else {
2801 VisitResult unititialized = VisitResult::TopTypeResult(
2802 "implicit parameter '" + implicit_name +
2803 "' is not defined when invoking " + callable->ReadableName() +
2804 " at " + PositionAsString(CurrentSourcePosition::Get()),
2805 callable->signature().parameter_types.types[i]);
2806 implicit_arguments.push_back(unititialized);
2807 }
2808 const Type* type = implicit_arguments.back().type();
2809 if (const TopType* top_type = TopType::DynamicCast(type)) {
2810 if (!callable->IsMacro() || callable->IsExternal()) {
2811 ReportError(
2812 "unititialized implicit parameters can only be passed to "
2813 "Torque-defined macros: the ",
2814 top_type->reason());
2815 }
2816 inline_macro = true;
2817 }
2818 }
2819
2820 std::vector<VisitResult> converted_arguments;
2821 StackRange argument_range = assembler().TopRange(0);
2822 std::vector<std::string> constexpr_arguments;
2823
2824 size_t current = 0;
2825 for (; current < callable->signature().implicit_count; ++current) {
2826 AddCallParameter(callable, implicit_arguments[current],
2827 callable->signature().parameter_types.types[current],
2828 &converted_arguments, &argument_range,
2829 &constexpr_arguments, inline_macro);
2830 }
2831
2832 if (this_reference) {
2833 DCHECK(callable->IsMethod());
2834 Method* method = Method::cast(callable);
2835 // By now, the this reference should either be a variable, a temporary or
2836 // a Slice. In either case the fetch of the VisitResult should succeed.
2837 VisitResult this_value = this_reference->GetVisitResult();
2838 if (inline_macro) {
2839 if (!this_value.type()->IsSubtypeOf(method->aggregate_type())) {
2840 ReportError("this parameter must be a subtype of ",
2841 *method->aggregate_type(), " but it is of type ",
2842 *this_value.type());
2843 }
2844 } else {
2845 AddCallParameter(callable, this_value, method->aggregate_type(),
2846 &converted_arguments, &argument_range,
2847 &constexpr_arguments, inline_macro);
2848 }
2849 ++current;
2850 }
2851
2852 for (const auto& arg : arguments.parameters) {
2853 const Type* to_type = (current >= callable->signature().types().size())
2854 ? TypeOracle::GetObjectType()
2855 : callable->signature().types()[current++];
2856 AddCallParameter(callable, arg, to_type, &converted_arguments,
2857 &argument_range, &constexpr_arguments, inline_macro);
2858 }
2859
2860 size_t label_count = callable->signature().labels.size();
2861 if (label_count != arguments.labels.size()) {
2862 std::stringstream s;
2863 s << "unexpected number of otherwise labels for "
2864 << callable->ReadableName() << " (expected "
2865 << std::to_string(label_count) << " found "
2866 << std::to_string(arguments.labels.size()) << ")";
2867 ReportError(s.str());
2868 }
2869
2870 if (callable->IsTransitioning()) {
2871 if (!CurrentCallable::Get()->IsTransitioning()) {
2872 std::stringstream s;
2873 s << *CurrentCallable::Get()
2874 << " isn't marked transitioning but calls the transitioning "
2875 << *callable;
2876 ReportError(s.str());
2877 }
2878 }
2879
2880 if (auto* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(callable)) {
2881 std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
2882 assembler().Emit(CallBuiltinInstruction{
2883 is_tailcall, builtin, argument_range.Size(), catch_block});
2884 GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
2885 if (is_tailcall) {
2886 return VisitResult::NeverResult();
2887 } else if (return_type->IsNever()) {
2888 assembler().Emit(AbortInstruction{AbortInstruction::Kind::kUnreachable});
2889 return VisitResult::NeverResult();
2890 } else {
2891 size_t slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
2892 if (builtin->IsStub()) {
2893 if (slot_count < 1 || slot_count > 2) {
2894 ReportError(
2895 "Builtin with stub linkage is expected to return one or two "
2896 "values but returns ",
2897 slot_count);
2898 }
2899 } else {
2900 if (slot_count != 1) {
2901 ReportError(
2902 "Builtin with JS linkage is expected to return one value but "
2903 "returns ",
2904 slot_count);
2905 }
2906 }
2907 return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(slot_count));
2908 }
2909 } else if (auto* macro = Macro::DynamicCast(callable)) {
2910 if (is_tailcall) {
2911 ReportError("can't tail call a macro");
2912 }
2913
2914 macro->SetUsed();
2915
2916 // If we're currently generating a C++ macro and it's calling another macro,
2917 // then we need to make sure that we also generate C++ code for the called
2918 // macro within the same -inl.inc file.
2919 if ((output_type_ == OutputType::kCC ||
2920 output_type_ == OutputType::kCCDebug) &&
2921 !inline_macro) {
2922 if (auto* torque_macro = TorqueMacro::DynamicCast(macro)) {
2923 auto* streams = CurrentFileStreams::Get();
2924 SourceId file = streams ? streams->file : SourceId::Invalid();
2925 GlobalContext::EnsureInCCOutputList(torque_macro, file);
2926 }
2927 }
2928
2929 // TODO(torque-builder): Consider a function builder here.
2930 if (return_type->IsConstexpr()) {
2931 DCHECK_EQ(0, arguments.labels.size());
2932 std::stringstream result;
2933 result << "(";
2934 bool first = true;
2935 switch (output_type_) {
2936 case OutputType::kCSA: {
2937 if (auto* extern_macro = ExternMacro::DynamicCast(macro)) {
2938 result << extern_macro->external_assembler_name() << "(state_)."
2939 << extern_macro->ExternalName() << "(";
2940 } else {
2941 result << macro->ExternalName() << "(state_";
2942 first = false;
2943 }
2944 break;
2945 }
2946 case OutputType::kCC: {
2947 auto* extern_macro = ExternMacro::DynamicCast(macro);
2948 CHECK_NOT_NULL(extern_macro);
2949 result << extern_macro->CCName() << "(";
2950 break;
2951 }
2952 case OutputType::kCCDebug: {
2953 auto* extern_macro = ExternMacro::DynamicCast(macro);
2954 CHECK_NOT_NULL(extern_macro);
2955 result << extern_macro->CCDebugName() << "(accessor";
2956 first = false;
2957 break;
2958 }
2959 }
2960 for (const VisitResult& arg : converted_arguments) {
2961 DCHECK(!arg.IsOnStack());
2962 if (!first) {
2963 result << ", ";
2964 }
2965 first = false;
2966 result << arg.constexpr_value();
2967 }
2968 result << "))";
2969 return VisitResult(return_type, result.str());
2970 } else if (inline_macro) {
2971 std::vector<Block*> label_blocks;
2972 label_blocks.reserve(arguments.labels.size());
2973 for (Binding<LocalLabel>* label : arguments.labels) {
2974 label_blocks.push_back(label->block);
2975 }
2976 return InlineMacro(macro, this_reference, converted_arguments,
2977 std::move(label_blocks));
2978 } else if (arguments.labels.empty() &&
2979 return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
2980 std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
2981 assembler().Emit(CallCsaMacroInstruction{
2982 macro, std::move(constexpr_arguments), catch_block});
2983 GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
2984 size_t return_slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
2985 return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(return_slot_count));
2986 } else {
2987 std::optional<Block*> return_continuation;
2988 if (return_type != TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
2989 return_continuation = assembler().NewBlock();
2990 }
2991
2992 std::vector<Block*> label_blocks;
2993
2994 for (size_t i = 0; i < label_count; ++i) {
2995 label_blocks.push_back(assembler().NewBlock());
2996 }
2997 std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
2998 assembler().Emit(CallCsaMacroAndBranchInstruction{
2999 macro, constexpr_arguments, return_continuation, label_blocks,
3000 catch_block});
3001 GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
3002
3003 for (size_t i = 0; i < label_count; ++i) {
3004 Binding<LocalLabel>* label = arguments.labels[i];
3005 size_t callee_label_parameters =
3006 callable->signature().labels[i].types.size();
3007 if (label->parameter_types.size() != callee_label_parameters) {
3008 std::stringstream s;
3009 s << "label " << label->name()
3010 << " doesn't have the right number of parameters (found "
3011 << std::to_string(label->parameter_types.size()) << " expected "
3012 << std::to_string(callee_label_parameters) << ")";
3013 ReportError(s.str());
3014 }
3015 assembler().Bind(label_blocks[i]);
3016 assembler().Goto(
3017 label->block,
3018 LowerParameterTypes(callable->signature().labels[i].types).size());
3019
3020 size_t j = 0;
3021 for (auto t : callable->signature().labels[i].types) {
3022 const Type* parameter_type = label->parameter_types[j];
3023 if (!t->IsSubtypeOf(parameter_type)) {
3024 ReportError("mismatch of label parameters (label expects ",
3025 *parameter_type, " but macro produces ", *t,
3026 " for parameter ", i + 1, ")");
3027 }
3028 j++;
3029 }
3030 }
3031
3032 if (return_continuation) {
3033 assembler().Bind(*return_continuation);
3034 size_t return_slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
3035 return VisitResult(return_type,
3036 assembler().TopRange(return_slot_count));
3037 } else {
3038 return VisitResult::NeverResult();
3039 }
3040 }
3041 } else if (auto* runtime_function = RuntimeFunction::DynamicCast(callable)) {
3042 std::optional<Block*> catch_block = GetCatchBlock();
3043 assembler().Emit(CallRuntimeInstruction{
3044 is_tailcall, runtime_function, argument_range.Size(), catch_block});
3045 GenerateCatchBlock(catch_block);
3046 if (is_tailcall || return_type == TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
3047 return VisitResult::NeverResult();
3048 } else {
3049 size_t slot_count = LoweredSlotCount(return_type);
3050 DCHECK_LE(slot_count, 1);
3051 // TODO(turbofan): Actually, runtime functions have to return a value, so
3052 // we should assert slot_count == 1 here.
3053 return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(slot_count));
3054 }
3055 } else if (auto* intrinsic = Intrinsic::DynamicCast(callable)) {
3056 if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%SizeOf") {
3057 if (specialization_types.size() != 1) {
3058 ReportError("%SizeOf must take a single type parameter");
3059 }
3060 const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3061 std::string size_string;
3062 if (std::optional<std::tuple<size_t, std::string>> size = SizeOf(type)) {
3063 size_string = std::get<1>(*size);
3064 } else {
3065 Error("size of ", *type, " is not known.");
3066 }
3067 return VisitResult(return_type, size_string);
3068 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%ClassHasMapConstant") {
3069 const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3070 const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3071 if (!class_type) {
3072 ReportError("%ClassHasMapConstant must take a class type parameter");
3073 }
3074 // If the class isn't actually used as the parameter to a TNode,
3075 // then we can't rely on the class existing in C++ or being of the same
3076 // type (e.g. it could be a template), so don't use the template CSA
3077 // machinery for accessing the class' map.
3078 if (class_type->name() != class_type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName()) {
3079 return VisitResult(return_type, std::string("false"));
3080 } else {
3081 return VisitResult(
3082 return_type,
3083 std::string("CodeStubAssembler(state_).ClassHasMapConstant<") +
3084 class_type->name() + ">()");
3085 }
3086 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%MinInstanceType") {
3087 if (specialization_types.size() != 1) {
3088 ReportError("%MinInstanceType must take a single type parameter");
3089 }
3090 const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3091 const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3092 if (!class_type) {
3093 ReportError("%MinInstanceType must take a class type parameter");
3094 }
3095 std::pair<std::string, std::string> instance_types =
3096 GetClassInstanceTypeRange(class_type);
3097 return VisitResult(return_type, instance_types.first);
3098 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%MaxInstanceType") {
3099 if (specialization_types.size() != 1) {
3100 ReportError("%MaxInstanceType must take a single type parameter");
3101 }
3102 const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3103 const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3104 if (!class_type) {
3105 ReportError("%MaxInstanceType must take a class type parameter");
3106 }
3107 std::pair<std::string, std::string> instance_types =
3108 GetClassInstanceTypeRange(class_type);
3109 return VisitResult(return_type, instance_types.second);
3110 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%RawConstexprCast") {
3111 if (intrinsic->signature().parameter_types.types.size() != 1 ||
3112 constexpr_arguments.size() != 1) {
3113 ReportError(
3114 "%RawConstexprCast must take a single parameter with constexpr "
3115 "type");
3116 }
3117 if (!return_type->IsConstexpr()) {
3118 std::stringstream s;
3119 s << *return_type
3120 << " return type for %RawConstexprCast is not constexpr";
3121 ReportError(s.str());
3122 }
3123 std::stringstream result;
3124 result << "static_cast<" << return_type->GetGeneratedTypeName() << ">(";
3125 result << constexpr_arguments[0];
3126 result << ")";
3127 return VisitResult(return_type, result.str());
3128 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%IndexedFieldLength") {
3129 const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3130 const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3131 if (!class_type) {
3132 ReportError("%IndexedFieldLength must take a class type parameter");
3133 }
3134 const Field& field =
3135 class_type->LookupField(StringLiteralUnquote(constexpr_arguments[0]));
3136 return GenerateArrayLength(VisitResult(type, argument_range), field);
3137 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%MakeLazy") {
3138 if (specialization_types[0]->IsStructType()) {
3139 ReportError("%MakeLazy can't use macros that return structs");
3140 }
3141 std::string getter_name = StringLiteralUnquote(constexpr_arguments[0]);
3142
3143 // Normally the parser would split namespace names for us, but we
3144 // sidestepped it by putting the macro name in a string literal.
3145 QualifiedName qualified_getter_name = QualifiedName::Parse(getter_name);
3146
3147 // converted_arguments contains all of the arguments to %MakeLazy. We're
3148 // looking for a function that takes all but the first.
3149 Arguments arguments_to_getter;
3150 arguments_to_getter.parameters.insert(
3151 arguments_to_getter.parameters.begin(),
3152 converted_arguments.begin() + 1, converted_arguments.end());
3153
3154 Callable* callable_macro = LookupCallable(
3155 qualified_getter_name, Declarations::Lookup(qualified_getter_name),
3156 arguments_to_getter, {});
3157 Macro* getter = Macro::DynamicCast(callable_macro);
3158 if (!getter || getter->IsMethod()) {
3159 ReportError(
3160 "%MakeLazy expects a macro, not builtin or other type of callable");
3161 }
3162 if (!getter->signature().labels.empty()) {
3163 ReportError("%MakeLazy requires a macro with no labels");
3164 }
3165 if (!getter->signature().return_type->IsSubtypeOf(
3166 specialization_types[0])) {
3167 ReportError("%MakeLazy expected return type ", *specialization_types[0],
3168 " but found ", *getter->signature().return_type);
3169 }
3170 if (getter->signature().implicit_count > 0) {
3171 ReportError("Implicit parameters are not yet supported in %MakeLazy");
3172 }
3173
3174 getter->SetUsed(); // Prevent warnings about unused macros.
3175
3176 // Now that we've looked up the getter macro, we have to convert the
3177 // arguments again, so that, for example, constexpr arguments can be
3178 // coerced to non-constexpr types and put on the stack.
3179
3180 std::vector<VisitResult> converted_arguments_for_getter;
3181 StackRange argument_range_for_getter = assembler().TopRange(0);
3182 std::vector<std::string> constexpr_arguments_for_getter;
3183
3184 size_t arg_count = 0;
3185 for (const auto& arg : arguments_to_getter.parameters) {
3186 DCHECK_LT(arg_count, getter->signature().types().size());
3187 const Type* to_type = getter->signature().types()[arg_count++];
3188 AddCallParameter(getter, arg, to_type, &converted_arguments_for_getter,
3189 &argument_range_for_getter,
3190 &constexpr_arguments_for_getter,
3191 /*inline_macro=*/false);
3192 }
3193
3194 // Now that the arguments are prepared, emit the instruction that consumes
3195 // them.
3196 assembler().Emit(MakeLazyNodeInstruction{
3197 getter, return_type, std::move(constexpr_arguments_for_getter)});
3198 return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(1));
3199 } else if (intrinsic->ExternalName() == "%FieldSlice") {
3200 const Type* type = specialization_types[0];
3201 const ClassType* class_type = ClassType::DynamicCast(type);
3202 if (!class_type) {
3203 ReportError("The first type parameter to %FieldSlice must be a class");
3204 }
3205 const Field& field =
3206 class_type->LookupField(StringLiteralUnquote(constexpr_arguments[0]));
3207 const Type* expected_slice_type =
3208 field.const_qualified
3209 ? TypeOracle::GetConstSliceType(field.name_and_type.type)
3210 : TypeOracle::GetMutableSliceType(field.name_and_type.type);
3211 const Type* declared_slice_type = specialization_types[1];
3212 if (expected_slice_type != declared_slice_type) {
3213 Error(
3214 "The second type parameter to %FieldSlice must be the precise "
3215 "slice type for the named field");
3216 }
3217 LocationReference ref = GenerateFieldReference(
3218 VisitResult(type, argument_range), field, class_type,
3219 /*treat_optional_as_indexed=*/true);
3220 if (!ref.IsHeapSlice()) {
3221 ReportError("%FieldSlice expected an indexed or optional field");
3222 }
3223 return ref.heap_slice();
3224 } else {
3225 assembler().Emit(CallIntrinsicInstruction{intrinsic, specialization_types,
3226 constexpr_arguments});
3227 size_t return_slot_count =
3228 LoweredSlotCount(intrinsic->signature().return_type);
3229 return VisitResult(return_type, assembler().TopRange(return_slot_count));
3230 }
3231 } else {
3232 UNREACHABLE();
3233 }
3234}

3236VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCall(
3237 const QualifiedName& callable_name, Arguments arguments,
3238 const TypeVector& specialization_types, bool is_tailcall) {
3239 Callable* callable =
3240 LookupCallable(callable_name, Declarations::Lookup(callable_name),
3241 arguments, specialization_types);
3242 return GenerateCall(callable, std::nullopt, arguments, specialization_types,
3243 is_tailcall);
3244}
3245
3246VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(CallExpression* expr,
3247 bool is_tailcall) {
3248 StackScope scope(this);
3249
3250 if (expr->callee->name->value == "&" && expr->arguments.size() == 1) {
3251 if (auto* loc_expr = LocationExpression::DynamicCast(expr->arguments[0])) {
3252 LocationReference ref = GetLocationReference(loc_expr);
3253 if (ref.IsHeapReference()) return scope.Yield(ref.heap_reference());
3254 if (ref.IsHeapSlice()) return scope.Yield(ref.heap_slice());
3255 }
3256 ReportError("Unable to create a heap reference.");
3257 }
3258
3259 Arguments arguments;
3260 QualifiedName name = QualifiedName(expr->callee->namespace_qualification,
3261 expr->callee->name->value);
3262 TypeVector specialization_types =
3263 TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->callee->generic_arguments);
3264 bool has_template_arguments = !specialization_types.empty();
3265 for (Expression* arg : expr->arguments)
3266 arguments.parameters.push_back(Visit(arg));
3267 arguments.labels = LabelsFromIdentifiers(expr->labels);
3268 if (!has_template_arguments && name.namespace_qualification.empty() &&
3269 TryLookupLocalValue(name.name)) {
3270 return scope.Yield(
3271 GeneratePointerCall(expr->callee, arguments, is_tailcall));
3272 } else {
3273 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
3274 Callable* callable = LookupCallable(name, Declarations::Lookup(name),
3275 arguments, specialization_types);
3276 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->callee->name->pos,
3277 callable->IdentifierPosition());
3278 }
3279 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
3280 Callable* callable = LookupCallable(name, Declarations::Lookup(name),
3281 arguments, specialization_types);
3282 Callable* caller = CurrentCallable::Get();
3283 KytheData::AddCall(caller, expr->callee->name->pos, callable);
3284 }
3285 if (expr->callee->name->value == "!" && arguments.parameters.size() == 1) {
3286 PropagateBitfieldMark(expr->arguments[0], expr);
3287 }
3288 if (expr->callee->name->value == "==" && arguments.parameters.size() == 2) {
3289 if (arguments.parameters[0].type()->IsConstexpr()) {
3290 PropagateBitfieldMark(expr->arguments[1], expr);
3291 } else if (arguments.parameters[1].type()->IsConstexpr()) {
3292 PropagateBitfieldMark(expr->arguments[0], expr);
3293 }
3294 }
3295 return scope.Yield(
3296 GenerateCall(name, arguments, specialization_types, is_tailcall));
3297 }
3298}

3300VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(CallMethodExpression* expr) {
3301 StackScope scope(this);
3302 Arguments arguments;
3303 std::string method_name = expr->method->name->value;
3304 TypeVector specialization_types =
3305 TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->method->generic_arguments);
3306 LocationReference target = GetLocationReference(expr->target);
3307 if (!target.IsVariableAccess()) {
3308 VisitResult result = GenerateFetchFromLocation(target);
3309 target = LocationReference::Temporary(result, "this parameter");
3310 }
3311 const AggregateType* target_type =
3312 (*target.ReferencedType())->AggregateSupertype().value_or(nullptr);
3313 if (!target_type) {
3314 ReportError("target of method call not a struct or class type");
3315 }
3316 for (Expression* arg : expr->arguments) {
3317 arguments.parameters.push_back(Visit(arg));
3318 }
3319 arguments.labels = LabelsFromIdentifiers(expr->labels);
3320 TypeVector argument_types = arguments.parameters.ComputeTypeVector();
3321 DCHECK_EQ(expr->method->namespace_qualification.size(), 0);
3322 QualifiedName qualified_name = QualifiedName(method_name);
3323 Callable* callable = LookupMethod(method_name, target_type, arguments, {});
3324 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
3325 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(expr->method->name->pos,
3326 callable->IdentifierPosition());
3327 }
3328 if (GlobalContext::collect_kythe_data()) {
3329 Callable* caller = CurrentCallable::Get();
3330 KytheData::AddCall(caller, expr->method->name->pos, callable);
3331 }
3332 return scope.Yield(GenerateCall(callable, target, arguments, {}, false));
3333}

3335VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::Visit(IntrinsicCallExpression* expr) {

3339 TypeVisitor::ComputeTypeVector(expr->generic_arguments);
3340 for (Expression* arg : expr->arguments)
3341 arguments.parameters.push_back(Visit(arg));
3342 return scope.Yield(
3343 GenerateCall(expr->name->value, arguments, specialization_types, false));

3369
3370VisitResult ImplementationVisitor::GenerateImplicitConvert(
3371 const Type* destination_type, VisitResult source) {
3372 StackScope scope(this);
3373 if (source.type() == TypeOracle::GetNeverType()) {
3374 ReportError("it is not allowed to use a value of type never");
3375 }
3376
3377 if (destination_type == source.type()) {
3378 return scope.Yield(GenerateCopy(source));
3379 }
3380
3381 if (auto from = TypeOracle::ImplicitlyConvertableFrom(destination_type,
3382 source.type())) {
3383 return scope.Yield(GenerateCall(kFromConstexprMacroName,
3384 Arguments{{source}, {}},
3385 {destination_type, *from}, false));
3386 } else if (IsAssignableFrom(destination_type, source.type())) {
3387 source.SetType(destination_type);
3388 return scope.Yield(GenerateCopy(source));
3389 } else {
3390 std::stringstream s;
3391 if (const TopType* top_type = TopType::DynamicCast(source.type())) {
3392 s << "undefined expression of type " << *destination_type << ": the "
3393 << top_type->reason();
3394 } else {
3395 s << "cannot use expression of type " << *source.type()
3396 << " as a value of type " << *destination_type;
3397 }
3398 ReportError(s.str());
3399 }

3407std::vector<Binding<LocalLabel>*> ImplementationVisitor::LabelsFromIdentifiers(
3408 const std::vector<Identifier*>& names) {
3409 std::vector<Binding<LocalLabel>*> result;
3410 result.reserve(names.size());
3411 for (const auto& name : names) {
3412 Binding<LocalLabel>* label = LookupLabel(name->value);
3413 result.push_back(label);
3414
3415 // Link up labels in "otherwise" part of the call expression with
3416 // either the label in the signature of the calling macro or the label
3417 // block ofa surrounding "try".
3418 if (GlobalContext::collect_language_server_data()) {
3419 LanguageServerData::AddDefinition(name->pos,
3420 label->declaration_position());
3421 }
3422 // TODO(v8:12261): Might have to track KytheData here.
3423 }
3424 return result;

3427StackRange ImplementationVisitor::LowerParameter(
3428 const Type* type, const std::string& parameter_name,
3429 Stack<std::string>* lowered_parameters) {
3430 if (std::optional<const StructType*> struct_type = type->StructSupertype()) {
3431 StackRange range = lowered_parameters->TopRange(0);
3432 for (auto& field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
3433 StackRange parameter_range = LowerParameter(
3434 field.name_and_type.type,
3435 parameter_name + "." + field.name_and_type.name, lowered_parameters);
3436 range.Extend(parameter_range);
3437 }
3438 return range;
3439 } else {
3440 lowered_parameters->Push(parameter_name);
3441 return lowered_parameters->TopRange(1);
3442 }
3443}

3475bool IsCompatibleSignature(const Signature& sig, const TypeVector& types,
3476 size_t label_count) {
3477 auto i = sig.parameter_types.types.begin() + sig.implicit_count;
3478 if ((sig.parameter_types.types.size() - sig.implicit_count) > types.size())
3479 return false;
3480 if (sig.labels.size() != label_count) return false;
3481 for (auto current : types) {
3482 if (i == sig.parameter_types.types.end()) {
3483 if (!sig.parameter_types.var_args) return false;
3484 if (!IsAssignableFrom(TypeOracle::GetObjectType(), current)) return false;
3485 } else {
3486 if (!IsAssignableFrom(*i++, current)) return false;
3487 }
3488 }
3489 return true;
3490}

3499
3500void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCatchBlock(
3501 std::optional<Block*> catch_block) {
3502 if (catch_block) {
3503 std::optional<Binding<LocalLabel>*> catch_handler =
3504 TryLookupLabel(kCatchLabelName);
3505 // Reset the local scopes to prevent the macro calls below from using the
3506 // current catch handler.
3507 BindingsManagersScope bindings_managers_scope;
3508 if (assembler().CurrentBlockIsComplete()) {
3509 assembler().Bind(*catch_block);
3510 GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
3511 "GetAndResetPendingMessage"),
3512 Arguments{{}, {}}, {}, false);
3513 assembler().Goto((*catch_handler)->block, 2);
3514 } else {
3515 CfgAssemblerScopedTemporaryBlock temp(&assembler(), *catch_block);
3516 GenerateCall(QualifiedName({TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING},
3517 "GetAndResetPendingMessage"),
3518 Arguments{{}, {}}, {}, false);
3519 assembler().Goto((*catch_handler)->block, 2);
3520 }
3521 }

3523void ImplementationVisitor::VisitAllDeclarables() {
3524 CurrentCallable::Scope current_callable(nullptr);
3525 const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Declarable>>& all_declarables =
3526 GlobalContext::AllDeclarables();
3527
3528 // This has to be an index-based loop because all_declarables can be extended
3529 // during the loop.
3530 for (size_t i = 0; i < all_declarables.size(); ++i) {
3531 try {
3532 Visit(all_declarables[i].get());
3533 } catch (TorqueAbortCompilation&) {
3534 // Recover from compile errors here. The error is recorded already.
3535 }
3536 }
3537
3538 // Do the same for macros which generate C++ code.
3539 output_type_ = OutputType::kCC;
3540 const std::vector<std::pair<TorqueMacro*, SourceId>>& cc_macros =
3541 GlobalContext::AllMacrosForCCOutput();
3542 for (size_t i = 0; i < cc_macros.size(); ++i) {
3543 try {
3544 Visit(static_cast<Declarable*>(cc_macros[i].first), cc_macros[i].second);
3545 } catch (TorqueAbortCompilation&) {
3546 // Recover from compile errors here. The error is recorded already.
3547 }
3548 }
3549
3550 // Do the same for macros which generate C++ debug code.
3551 // The set of macros is the same as C++ macros.
3552 output_type_ = OutputType::kCCDebug;
3553 const std::vector<std::pair<TorqueMacro*, SourceId>>& cc_debug_macros =
3554 GlobalContext::AllMacrosForCCDebugOutput();
3555 for (size_t i = 0; i < cc_debug_macros.size(); ++i) {
3556 try {
3557 Visit(static_cast<Declarable*>(cc_debug_macros[i].first),
3558 cc_debug_macros[i].second);
3559 } catch (TorqueAbortCompilation&) {
3560 // Recover from compile errors here. The error is recorded already.
3561 }
3562 }
3563
3564 output_type_ = OutputType::kCSA;
3565}
3566
3567void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Declarable* declarable,
3568 std::optional<SourceId> file) {
3569 CurrentScope::Scope current_scope(declarable->ParentScope());
3570 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(declarable->Position());
3571 CurrentFileStreams::Scope current_file_streams(
3572 &GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(file ? *file
3573 : declarable->Position().source));
3574 if (Callable* callable = Callable::DynamicCast(declarable)) {
3575 if (!callable->ShouldGenerateExternalCode(output_type_))
3576 CurrentFileStreams::Get() = nullptr;
3577 }
3578 switch (declarable->kind()) {
3579 case Declarable::kExternMacro:
3580 return Visit(ExternMacro::cast(declarable));
3581 case Declarable::kTorqueMacro:
3582 return Visit(TorqueMacro::cast(declarable));
3583 case Declarable::kMethod:
3584 return Visit(Method::cast(declarable));
3585 case Declarable::kBuiltin:
3586 return Visit(Builtin::cast(declarable));
3587 case Declarable::kTypeAlias:
3588 return Visit(TypeAlias::cast(declarable));
3589 case Declarable::kNamespaceConstant:
3590 return Visit(NamespaceConstant::cast(declarable));
3591 case Declarable::kRuntimeFunction:
3592 case Declarable::kIntrinsic:
3593 case Declarable::kExternConstant:
3594 case Declarable::kNamespace:
3595 case Declarable::kGenericCallable:
3596 case Declarable::kGenericType:
3597 return;
3598 }
3599}

3613
3614void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBuiltinDefinitionsAndInterfaceDescriptors(
3615 const std::string& output_directory) {
3616 std::stringstream builtin_definitions;
3617 std::string builtin_definitions_file_name = "builtin-definitions.h";
3618
3619 // This file contains plain interface descriptor definitions and has to be
3620 // included in the middle of interface-descriptors.h. Thus it is not a normal
3621 // header file and uses the .inc suffix instead of the .h suffix.
3622 std::stringstream interface_descriptors;
3623 std::string interface_descriptors_file_name = "interface-descriptors.inc";
3624 {
3625 IncludeGuardScope builtin_definitions_include_guard(
3626 builtin_definitions, builtin_definitions_file_name);
3627
3628 builtin_definitions
3629 << "\n"
3630 "#define BUILTIN_LIST_FROM_TORQUE(CPP, TFJ, TFC, TFS, TFH, "
3631 "ASM) "
3632 "\\\n";
3633 for (auto& declarable : GlobalContext::AllDeclarables()) {
3634 Builtin* builtin = Builtin::DynamicCast(declarable.get());
3635 if (!builtin || builtin->IsExternal()) continue;
3636 if (builtin->IsStub()) {
3637 builtin_definitions << "TFC(" << builtin->ExternalName() << ", "
3638 << builtin->ExternalName();
3639 if (!builtin->HasCustomInterfaceDescriptor()) {
3640 std::string descriptor_name = builtin->ExternalName() + "Descriptor";
3641 bool has_context_parameter =
3642 builtin->signature().HasContextParameter();
3643 size_t kFirstNonContextParameter = has_context_parameter ? 1 : 0;
3644 TypeVector return_types = LowerType(builtin->signature().return_type);
3645
3646 interface_descriptors << "class " << descriptor_name
3647 << " : public StaticCallInterfaceDescriptor<"
3648 << descriptor_name << "> {\n";
3649
3650 interface_descriptors << " public:\n";
3651
3652 // Currently, no torque-defined builtins are directly exposed to
3653 // objects inside the sandbox via the code pointer table.
3654 interface_descriptors << " INTERNAL_DESCRIPTOR()\n";
3655
3656 if (has_context_parameter) {
3657 interface_descriptors << " DEFINE_RESULT_AND_PARAMETERS(";
3658 } else {
3659 interface_descriptors
3660 << " DEFINE_RESULT_AND_PARAMETERS_NO_CONTEXT(";
3661 }
3662 interface_descriptors << return_types.size();
3663 for (size_t i = kFirstNonContextParameter;
3664 i < builtin->parameter_names().size(); ++i) {
3665 Identifier* parameter = builtin->parameter_names()[i];
3666 interface_descriptors << ", k" << CamelifyString(parameter->value);
3667 }
3668 interface_descriptors << ")\n";
3669
3670 interface_descriptors << " DEFINE_RESULT_AND_PARAMETER_TYPES(";
3671 PrintCommaSeparatedList(interface_descriptors, return_types,
3672 MachineTypeString);
3673 bool is_first = return_types.empty();
3674 for (size_t i = kFirstNonContextParameter;
3675 i < builtin->parameter_names().size(); ++i) {
3676 const Type* type = builtin->signature().parameter_types.types[i];
3677 interface_descriptors << (is_first ? "" : ", ")
3678 << MachineTypeString(type);
3679 is_first = false;
3680 }
3681 interface_descriptors << ")\n";
3682
3683 interface_descriptors << " DECLARE_DEFAULT_DESCRIPTOR("
3684 << descriptor_name << ")\n";
3685 interface_descriptors << "};\n\n";
3686 }
3687 } else {
3688 builtin_definitions << "TFJ(" << builtin->ExternalName();
3689 if (builtin->IsVarArgsJavaScript()) {
3690 builtin_definitions << ", kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel";
3691 } else {
3692 DCHECK(builtin->IsFixedArgsJavaScript());
3693 // FixedArg javascript builtins need to offer the parameter
3694 // count.
3695 int parameter_count =
3696 static_cast<int>(builtin->signature().ExplicitCount());
3697 builtin_definitions << ", JSParameterCount(" << parameter_count
3698 << ")";
3699 // And the receiver is explicitly declared.
3700 builtin_definitions << ", kReceiver";
3701 for (size_t i = builtin->signature().implicit_count;
3702 i < builtin->parameter_names().size(); ++i) {
3703 Identifier* parameter = builtin->parameter_names()[i];
3704 builtin_definitions << ", k" << CamelifyString(parameter->value);
3705 }
3706 }
3707 }
3708 builtin_definitions << ") \\\n";
3709 }
3710 builtin_definitions << "\n";
3711
3712 builtin_definitions
3713 << "#define TORQUE_FUNCTION_POINTER_TYPE_TO_BUILTIN_MAP(V) \\\n";
3714 for (const BuiltinPointerType* type :
3715 TypeOracle::AllBuiltinPointerTypes()) {
3716 Builtin* example_builtin =
3717 Declarations::FindSomeInternalBuiltinWithType(type);
3718 if (!example_builtin) {
3719 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(
3720 SourcePosition{CurrentSourceFile::Get(), LineAndColumn::Invalid(),
3721 LineAndColumn::Invalid()});
3722 ReportError("unable to find any builtin with type \"", *type, "\"");
3723 }
3724 builtin_definitions << " V(" << type->function_pointer_type_id() << ","
3725 << example_builtin->ExternalName() << ")\\\n";
3726 }
3727 builtin_definitions << "\n";
3728 }
3729 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + builtin_definitions_file_name,
3730 builtin_definitions.str());
3731 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + interface_descriptors_file_name,
3732 interface_descriptors.str());
3733}

3735namespace {
3736
3737enum class FieldSectionType : uint32_t {
3738 kNoSection = 0,
3739 kWeakSection = 1 << 0,
3740 kStrongSection = 2 << 0,
3741 kScalarSection = 3 << 0
3742};
3743
3744bool IsPointerSection(FieldSectionType type) {
3745 return type == FieldSectionType::kWeakSection ||
3746 type == FieldSectionType::kStrongSection;
3747}
3748
3749using FieldSections = base::Flags<FieldSectionType>;
3750
3751std::string ToString(FieldSectionType type) {
3752 switch (type) {
3753 case FieldSectionType::kNoSection:
3754 return "NoSection";
3755 case FieldSectionType::kWeakSection:
3756 return "WeakFields";
3757 case FieldSectionType::kStrongSection:
3758 return "StrongFields";
3759 case FieldSectionType::kScalarSection:
3760 return "ScalarFields";
3761 }
3762 UNREACHABLE();
3763}
3764
3765class FieldOffsetsGenerator {
3766 public:
3767 explicit FieldOffsetsGenerator(const ClassType* type) : type_(type) {}
3768
3769 virtual void WriteField(const Field& f, const std::string& size_string) = 0;
3770 virtual void WriteFieldOffsetGetter(const Field& f) = 0;
3771 virtual void WriteMarker(const std::string& marker) = 0;
3772
3773 virtual ~FieldOffsetsGenerator() { CHECK(is_finished_); }
3774
3775 void RecordOffsetFor(const Field& f) {
3776 CHECK(!is_finished_);
3777 UpdateSection(f);
3778
3779 // Emit kHeaderSize before any indexed field.
3780 if (f.index.has_value() && !header_size_emitted_) {
3781 WriteMarker("kHeaderSize");
3782 header_size_emitted_ = true;
3783 }
3784
3785 // We don't know statically how much space an indexed field takes, so report
3786 // it as zero.
3787 std::string size_string = "0";
3788 if (!f.index.has_value()) {
3789 size_t field_size;
3790 std::tie(field_size, size_string) = f.GetFieldSizeInformation();
3791 }
3792 if (f.offset.has_value()) {
3793 WriteField(f, size_string);
3794 } else {
3795 WriteFieldOffsetGetter(f);
3796 }
3797 }
3798
3799 void Finish() {
3800 End(current_section_);
3801 if (!(completed_sections_ & FieldSectionType::kWeakSection)) {
3802 Begin(FieldSectionType::kWeakSection);
3803 End(FieldSectionType::kWeakSection);
3804 }
3805 if (!(completed_sections_ & FieldSectionType::kStrongSection)) {
3806 Begin(FieldSectionType::kStrongSection);
3807 End(FieldSectionType::kStrongSection);
3808 }
3809 is_finished_ = true;
3810
3811 // In the presence of indexed fields, we already emitted kHeaderSize before
3812 // the indexed field.
3813 if (!type_->IsShape() && !header_size_emitted_) {
3814 WriteMarker("kHeaderSize");
3815 }
3816 if (!type_->IsAbstract() && type_->HasStaticSize()) {
3817 WriteMarker("kSize");
3818 }
3819 }
3820
3821 protected:
3822 const ClassType* type_;
3823
3824 private:
3825 FieldSectionType GetSectionFor(const Field& f) {
3826 const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
3827 if (field_type == TypeOracle::GetVoidType()) {
3828 // Allow void type for marker constants of size zero.
3829 return current_section_;
3830 }
3831 StructType::Classification struct_contents =
3832 StructType::ClassificationFlag::kEmpty;
3833 if (auto field_as_struct = field_type->StructSupertype()) {
3834 struct_contents = (*field_as_struct)->ClassifyContents();
3835 }
3836 if ((struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged) &&
3837 (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kWeakTagged)) {
3838 // It's okay for a struct to contain both strong and weak data. We'll just
3839 // treat the whole thing as weak. This is required for DescriptorEntry.
3840 struct_contents &= ~StructType::Classification(
3841 StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged);
3842 }
3843 bool struct_contains_tagged_fields =
3844 (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged) ||
3845 (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kWeakTagged);
3846 if (struct_contains_tagged_fields &&
3847 (struct_contents & StructType::ClassificationFlag::kUntagged)) {
3848 // We can't declare what section a struct goes in if it has multiple
3849 // categories of data within.
3850 Error(
3851 "Classes do not support fields which are structs containing both "
3852 "tagged and untagged data.")
3853 .Position(f.pos);
3854 }
3855 if ((field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetStrongTaggedType()) ||
3856 struct_contents == StructType::ClassificationFlag::kStrongTagged) &&
3857 !f.custom_weak_marking) {
3858 return FieldSectionType::kStrongSection;
3859 } else if (field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) ||
3860 struct_contains_tagged_fields) {
3861 return FieldSectionType::kWeakSection;
3862 } else {
3863 return FieldSectionType::kScalarSection;
3864 }
3865 }
3866 void UpdateSection(const Field& f) {
3867 FieldSectionType type = GetSectionFor(f);
3868 if (current_section_ == type) return;
3869 if (IsPointerSection(type)) {
3870 if (completed_sections_ & type) {
3871 std::stringstream s;
3872 s << "cannot declare field " << f.name_and_type.name << " in class "
3873 << type_->name() << ", because section " << ToString(type)
3874 << " to which it belongs has already been finished.";
3875 Error(s.str()).Position(f.pos);
3876 }
3877 }
3878 End(current_section_);
3879 current_section_ = type;
3880 Begin(current_section_);
3881 }
3882 void Begin(FieldSectionType type) {
3883 DCHECK(type != FieldSectionType::kNoSection);
3884 if (!IsPointerSection(type)) return;
3885 WriteMarker("kStartOf" + ToString(type) + "Offset");
3886 }
3887 void End(FieldSectionType type) {
3888 if (!IsPointerSection(type)) return;
3889 completed_sections_ |= type;
3890 WriteMarker("kEndOf" + ToString(type) + "Offset");
3891 }
3892
3893 FieldSectionType current_section_ = FieldSectionType::kNoSection;
3894 FieldSections completed_sections_ = FieldSectionType::kNoSection;
3895 bool is_finished_ = false;
3896 bool header_size_emitted_ = false;
3897};

3903 ", " + super->name() + ">";

3955void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBitFields(
3956 const std::string& output_directory) {
3957 std::stringstream header;
3958 std::string file_name = "bit-fields.h";
3959 {
3960 IncludeGuardScope include_guard(header, file_name);
3961 header << "#include \"src/base/bit-field.h\"\n\n";
3962 NamespaceScope namespaces(header, {"v8", "internal"});
3963
3964 for (const auto& type : TypeOracle::GetBitFieldStructTypes()) {
3965 bool all_single_bits = true; // Track whether every field is one bit.
3966 header << "// " << type->GetPosition() << "\n";
3967 header << "#define DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_"
3968 << CapifyStringWithUnderscores(type->name()) << "() \\\n";
3969 std::string type_name = type->GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName();
3970 for (const auto& field : type->fields()) {
3971 const char* suffix = field.num_bits == 1 ? "Bit" : "Bits";
3972 all_single_bits = all_single_bits && field.num_bits == 1;
3973 std::string field_type_name =
3974 field.name_and_type.type->GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName();
3975 header << " using " << CamelifyString(field.name_and_type.name)
3976 << suffix << " = base::BitField<" << field_type_name << ", "
3977 << field.offset << ", " << field.num_bits << ", " << type_name
3978 << ">; \\\n";
3979 }
3980
3981 // If every field is one bit, we can also generate a convenient enum.
3982 if (all_single_bits) {
3983 header << " enum Flag: " << type_name << " { \\\n";
3984 header << " kNone = 0, \\\n";
3985 for (const auto& field : type->fields()) {
3986 header << " k" << CamelifyString(field.name_and_type.name) << " = "
3987 << type_name << "{1} << " << field.offset << ", \\\n";
3988 }
3989 header << " }; \\\n";
3990 header << " using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>; \\\n";
3991 header << " static constexpr int kFlagCount = "
3992 << type->fields().size() << "; \\\n";
3993 }
3994
3995 header << "\n";
3996 }
3997 }
3998 const std::string output_header_path = output_directory + "/" + file_name;
3999 WriteFile(output_header_path, header.str());
4000}

4004class ClassFieldOffsetGenerator : public FieldOffsetsGenerator {
4005 public:
4006 ClassFieldOffsetGenerator(std::ostream& header, std::ostream& inline_header,
4007 const ClassType* type, std::string gen_name,
4008 const ClassType* parent, bool use_templates = true)
4009 : FieldOffsetsGenerator(type),
4010 hdr_(header),
4011 inl_(inline_header),
4012 previous_field_end_(FirstFieldStart(type, parent, use_templates)),
4013 gen_name_(gen_name) {}
4014
4015 void WriteField(const Field& f, const std::string& size_string) override {
4016 hdr_ << " // " << f.pos << "\n";
4017 std::string field = "k" + CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4018 std::string field_end = field + "End";
4019 hdr_ << " static constexpr int " << field << " = " << previous_field_end_
4020 << ";\n";
4021 hdr_ << " static constexpr int " << field_end << " = " << field << " + "
4022 << size_string << " - 1;\n";
4023 previous_field_end_ = field_end + " + 1";
4024 }
4025
4026 void WriteFieldOffsetGetter(const Field& f) override {
4027 // A static constexpr int is more convenient than a getter if the offset is
4028 // known.
4029 DCHECK(!f.offset.has_value());
4030
4031 std::string function_name = CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4032
4033 std::vector<cpp::TemplateParameter> params = {cpp::TemplateParameter("D"),
4034 cpp::TemplateParameter("P")};
4035 cpp::Class owner(std::move(params), gen_name_);
4036
4037 auto getter = cpp::Function::DefaultGetter("int", &owner, function_name);
4038 getter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4039 getter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4040 // Item 1 in a flattened slice is the offset.
4041 stream << " return static_cast<int>(std::get<1>("
4042 << Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(type_->GetSliceMacroName(f))
4043 << "(*static_cast<const D*>(this))));\n";
4044 });
4045 }
4046 void WriteMarker(const std::string& marker) override {
4047 hdr_ << " static constexpr int " << marker << " = " << previous_field_end_
4048 << ";\n";
4049 }
4050
4051 private:
4052 static std::string FirstFieldStart(const ClassType* type,
4053 const ClassType* parent,
4054 bool use_templates = true) {
4055 std::string parent_name = use_templates ? "P" : parent->name();
4056
4057 if (type->IsLayoutDefinedInCpp()) {
4058 // TODO(leszeks): Hacked in support for some classes (e.g.
4059 // HeapObject) being mirrored by a *Layout class. Remove once
4060 // everything is ported to layout classes.
4061 if (parent_name == "HeapObject" || parent_name == "TrustedObject") {
4062 parent_name += "Layout";
4063 }
4064
4065 return "sizeof(" + parent_name + ")";
4066 }
4067
4068 if (parent && parent->IsShape()) {
4069 return parent_name + "::kSize";
4070 }
4071 return parent_name + "::kHeaderSize";
4072 }
4073
4074 std::ostream& hdr_;
4075 std::ostream& inl_;
4076 std::string previous_field_end_;
4077 std::string gen_name_;
4078};

4136std::optional<std::vector<Field>> GetOrderedUniqueIndexFields(
4137 const ClassType& type) {
4138 std::vector<Field> result;
4139 std::set<std::string> index_names;
4140 for (const Field& field : type.ComputeAllFields()) {
4141 if (field.index) {
4142 auto name_and_type = ExtractSimpleFieldArraySize(type, field.index->expr);
4143 if (!name_and_type) {
4144 return std::nullopt;
4145 }
4146 index_names.insert(name_and_type->name);
4147 }
4148 }
4149
4150 for (const Field& field : type.ComputeAllFields()) {
4151 if (index_names.count(field.name_and_type.name) != 0) {
4152 result.push_back(field);
4153 }
4154 }
4155
4156 return result;

4159void CppClassGenerator::GenerateClass() {
4160 // Is<name>_NonInline(Tagged<HeapObject>)
4161 if (!type_->IsShape()) {
4162 cpp::Function f("Is"s + name_ + "_NonInline");
4163 f.SetDescription("Alias for Is"s + name_ + "() that avoids inlining.");
4164 f.SetExport(true);
4165 f.SetReturnType("bool");
4166 f.AddParameter("Tagged<HeapObject>", "o");
4167
4168 f.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4169 hdr_ << "\n";
4170 f.PrintDefinition(impl_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4171 stream << " return Is" << name_ << "(o);\n";
4172 });
4173 }
4174 hdr_ << "// Definition " << Position() << "\n";
4175 hdr_ << template_decl() << "\n";
4176 hdr_ << "class " << gen_name_ << " : public P {\n";
4177 hdr_ << " static_assert(\n"
4178 << " std::is_same<" << name_ << ", D>::value,\n"
4179 << " \"Use this class as direct base for " << name_ << ".\");\n";
4180 hdr_ << " static_assert(\n"
4181 << " std::is_same<" << super_->name() << ", P>::value,\n"
4182 << " \"Pass in " << super_->name()
4183 << " as second template parameter for " << gen_name_ << ".\");\n\n";
4184 hdr_ << " public: \n";
4185 hdr_ << " using Super = P;\n";
4186 hdr_ << " using TorqueGeneratedClass = " << gen_name_ << "<D,P>;\n\n";
4187 if (!type_->ShouldExport() && !type_->IsExtern()) {
4188 hdr_ << " protected: // not extern or @export\n";
4189 }
4190 for (const Field& f : type_->fields()) {
4191 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(f.pos);
4192 std::vector<const Field*> struct_fields;
4193 GenerateFieldAccessors(f, struct_fields);
4194 }
4195 if (!type_->ShouldExport() && !type_->IsExtern()) {
4196 hdr_ << " public:\n";
4197 }
4198
4199 std::vector<cpp::TemplateParameter> templateArgs = {
4200 cpp::TemplateParameter("D"), cpp::TemplateParameter("P")};
4201 cpp::Class c(std::move(templateArgs), gen_name_);
4202
4203 if (type_->ShouldGeneratePrint()) {
4204 hdr_ << " DECL_PRINTER(" << name_ << ")\n\n";
4205 }
4206
4207 if (type_->ShouldGenerateVerify()) {
4208 IfDefScope hdr_scope(hdr_, "VERIFY_HEAP");
4209 // V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void Verify(Isolate*);
4210 cpp::Function f(&c, name_ + "Verify");
4211 f.SetExport();
4212 f.SetReturnType("void");
4213 f.AddParameter("Isolate*", "isolate");
4214 f.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4215
4216 IfDefScope impl_scope(impl_, "VERIFY_HEAP");
4217 impl_ << "\ntemplate <>\n";
4218 impl_ << "void " << gen_name_I_ << "::" << name_
4219 << "Verify(Isolate* isolate) {\n";
4220 impl_ << " TorqueGeneratedClassVerifiers::" << name_ << "Verify(Cast<"
4221 << name_
4222 << ">(*this), "
4223 "isolate);\n";
4224 impl_ << "}\n\n";
4225 impl_ << "\n";
4226 }
4227
4228 hdr_ << "\n";
4229 ClassFieldOffsetGenerator g(hdr_, inl_, type_, gen_name_,
4230 type_->GetSuperClass());
4231 for (const auto& f : type_->fields()) {
4232 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope scope(f.pos);
4233 g.RecordOffsetFor(f);
4234 }
4235 g.Finish();
4236 hdr_ << "\n";
4237
4238 auto index_fields = GetOrderedUniqueIndexFields(*type_);
4239
4240 if (!index_fields.has_value()) {
4241 hdr_ << " // SizeFor implementations not generated due to complex array "
4242 "lengths\n\n";
4243
4244 const Field& last_field = type_->LastField();
4245 std::string last_field_item_size =
4246 std::get<1>(*SizeOf(last_field.name_and_type.type));
4247
4248 // int AllocatedSize() const
4249 {
4250 cpp::Function f =
4251 cpp::Function::DefaultGetter("int", &c, "AllocatedSize");
4252 f.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4253
4254 f.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4255 stream << " auto slice = "
4256 << Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(
4257 type_->GetSliceMacroName(last_field))
4258 << "(*static_cast<const D*>(this));\n";
4259 stream << " return static_cast<int>(std::get<1>(slice)) + "
4260 << last_field_item_size
4261 << " * static_cast<int>(std::get<2>(slice));\n";
4262 });
4263 }
4264 } else if (type_->ShouldGenerateBodyDescriptor() ||
4265 (!type_->IsAbstract() &&
4266 !type_->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetJSObjectType()))) {
4267 cpp::Function f(&c, "SizeFor");
4268 f.SetReturnType("int32_t");
4269 f.SetFlags(cpp::Function::kStatic | cpp::Function::kConstexpr |
4270 cpp::Function::kV8Inline);
4271 for (const Field& field : *index_fields) {
4272 f.AddParameter("int", field.name_and_type.name);
4273 }
4274 f.PrintInlineDefinition(hdr_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4275 if (index_fields->empty()) {
4276 stream << " DCHECK(kHeaderSize == kSize && kHeaderSize == "
4277 << *type_->size().SingleValue() << ");\n";
4278 }
4279 stream << " int32_t size = kHeaderSize;\n";
4280 for (const Field& field : type_->ComputeAllFields()) {
4281 if (field.index) {
4282 auto index_name_and_type =
4283 *ExtractSimpleFieldArraySize(*type_, field.index->expr);
4284 stream << " size += " << index_name_and_type.name << " * "
4285 << std::get<0>(field.GetFieldSizeInformation()) << ";\n";
4286 }
4287 }
4288 if (type_->size().Alignment() < TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize()) {
4289 stream << " size = OBJECT_POINTER_ALIGN(size);\n";
4290 }
4291 stream << " return size;\n";
4292 });
4293
4294 // V8_INLINE int32_t AllocatedSize() const
4295 {
4296 cpp::Function allocated_size_f =
4297 cpp::Function::DefaultGetter("int32_t", &c, "AllocatedSize");
4298 allocated_size_f.SetFlag(cpp::Function::kV8Inline);
4299 allocated_size_f.PrintInlineDefinition(hdr_, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
4300 stream << " return SizeFor(";
4301 bool first = true;
4302 for (const auto& field : *index_fields) {
4303 if (!first) stream << ", ";
4304 stream << "this->" << field.name_and_type.name << "()";
4305 first = false;
4306 }
4307 stream << ");\n";
4308 });
4309 }
4310 }
4311
4312 hdr_ << " friend class Factory;\n\n";
4313
4314 GenerateClassConstructors();
4315
4316 hdr_ << "};\n\n";
4317
4318 if (type_->ShouldGenerateFullClassDefinition()) {
4319 // If this class extends from another class which is defined in the same tq
4320 // file, and that other class doesn't generate a full class definition, then
4321 // the resulting .inc file would be uncompilable due to ordering
4322 // requirements: the generated file must go before the hand-written
4323 // definition of the base class, but it must also go after that same
4324 // hand-written definition.
4325 std::optional<const ClassType*> parent = type_->parent()->ClassSupertype();
4326 while (parent) {
4327 if ((*parent)->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions() &&
4328 !(*parent)->ShouldGenerateFullClassDefinition() &&
4329 (*parent)->AttributedToFile() == type_->AttributedToFile()) {
4330 Error("Exported ", *type_,
4331 " cannot be in the same file as its parent extern ", **parent);
4332 }
4333 parent = (*parent)->parent()->ClassSupertype();
4334 }
4335
4336 GenerateClassExport(type_, hdr_, inl_);
4337 }
4338}

4403void CppClassGenerator::GenerateClassConstructors() {
4404 const ClassType* typecheck_type = type_;
4405 while (typecheck_type->IsShape()) {
4406 typecheck_type = typecheck_type->GetSuperClass();
4407
4408 // Shapes have already been checked earlier to inherit from JSObject, so we
4409 // should have found an appropriate type.
4410 DCHECK(typecheck_type);
4411 }
4412
4413 hdr_ << " template <class DAlias = D>\n";
4414 hdr_ << " constexpr " << gen_name_ << "() : P() {\n";
4415 hdr_ << " static_assert(\n";
4416 hdr_ << " std::is_base_of<" << gen_name_ << ", DAlias>::value,\n";
4417 hdr_ << " \"class " << gen_name_
4418 << " should be used as direct base for " << name_ << ".\");\n";
4419 hdr_ << " }\n\n";
4420
4421 hdr_ << " protected:\n";
4422 hdr_ << " inline explicit constexpr " << gen_name_
4423 << "(Address ptr, typename P::SkipTypeCheckTag\n)";
4424 hdr_ << " : P(ptr, typename P::SkipTypeCheckTag{}) {}\n";
4425 hdr_ << " inline explicit " << gen_name_ << "(Address ptr);\n";
4426
4427 inl_ << "template<class D, class P>\n";
4428 inl_ << "inline " << gen_name_T_ << "::" << gen_name_ << "(Address ptr)\n";
4429 inl_ << " : P(ptr) {\n";
4430 inl_ << " SLOW_DCHECK(Is" << typecheck_type->name()
4431 << "_NonInline(*this));\n";
4432 inl_ << "}\n";
4433}

4435namespace {
4436std::string GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(const Type* type,
4437 const std::string& value) {
4438 bool maybe_object = !type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetStrongTaggedType());
4439 std::stringstream type_check;
4440 bool at_start = true;
4441 // If weak pointers are allowed, then start by checking for a cleared value.
4442 if (maybe_object) {
4443 type_check << value << ".IsCleared()";
4444 at_start = false;
4445 }
4446 for (const TypeChecker& runtime_type : type->GetTypeCheckers()) {
4447 if (!at_start) type_check << " || ";
4448 at_start = false;
4449 if (maybe_object) {
4450 bool strong = runtime_type.weak_ref_to.empty();
4451 if (strong && runtime_type.type == WEAK_HEAP_OBJECT) {
4452 // Rather than a generic Weak<T>, this is the basic type WeakHeapObject.
4453 // We can't validate anything more about the type of the object pointed
4454 // to, so just check that it's weak.
4455 type_check << value << ".IsWeak()";
4456 } else {
4457 type_check << "(" << (strong ? "!" : "") << value << ".IsWeak() && Is"
4458 << (strong ? runtime_type.type : runtime_type.weak_ref_to)
4459 << "(" << value << ".GetHeapObjectOrSmi()))";
4460 }
4461 } else {
4462 type_check << "Is" << runtime_type.type << "(" << value << ")";
4463 }
4464 }
4465 return type_check.str();
4466}
4467
4468void GenerateBoundsDCheck(std::ostream& os, const std::string& index,
4469 const ClassType* type, const Field& f) {
4470 os << " DCHECK_GE(" << index << ", 0);\n";
4471 std::string length_expression;
4472 if (std::optional<NameAndType> array_length =
4473 ExtractSimpleFieldArraySize(*type, f.index->expr)) {
4474 length_expression = "this ->" + array_length->name + "()";
4475 } else {
4476 // The length is element 2 in the flattened field slice.
4477 length_expression =
4478 "static_cast<int>(std::get<2>(" +
4479 Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(type->GetSliceMacroName(f)) +
4480 "(*static_cast<const D*>(this))))";
4481 }
4482 os << " DCHECK_LT(" << index << ", " << length_expression << ");\n";
4483}

4485bool CanGenerateFieldAccessors(const Type* field_type) {
4486 // float64_or_hole should be treated like float64. For now, we don't need it.
4487 // TODO(v8:10391) Generate accessors for external pointers.
4488 return field_type != TypeOracle::GetVoidType() &&
4489 field_type != TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrHoleType() &&
4490 !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetExternalPointerType()) &&
4491 !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTrustedPointerType()) &&
4492 !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetProtectedPointerType());
4493}
