4496// TODO(sigurds): Keep in sync with DECL_ACCESSORS and ACCESSORS macro.
4497void CppClassGenerator::GenerateFieldAccessors(
4498 const Field& class_field, std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields) {
4499 const Field& innermost_field =
4500 struct_fields.empty() ? class_field : *struct_fields.back();
4501 const Type* field_type = innermost_field.name_and_type.type;
4502 if (!CanGenerateFieldAccessors(field_type)) return;
4503
4504 if (const StructType* struct_type = StructType::DynamicCast(field_type)) {
4505 struct_fields.resize(struct_fields.size() + 1);
4506 for (const Field& struct_field : struct_type->fields()) {
4507 struct_fields[struct_fields.size() - 1] = &struct_field;
4508 GenerateFieldAccessors(class_field, struct_fields);
4509 }
4510 struct_fields.resize(struct_fields.size() - 1);
4511 return;
4512 }
4513
4514 bool indexed = class_field.index && !class_field.index->optional;
4515 std::string type_name = GetTypeNameForAccessor(innermost_field);
4516 bool can_contain_heap_objects = CanContainHeapObjects(field_type);
4517
4518 // Assemble an accessor name by accumulating together all of the nested field
4519 // names.
4520 std::string name = class_field.name_and_type.name;
4521 for (const Field* nested_struct_field : struct_fields) {
4522 name += "_" + nested_struct_field->name_and_type.name;
4523 }
4524
4525 // Generate declarations in header.
4526 if (can_contain_heap_objects && !field_type->IsClassType() &&
4527 !field_type->IsStructType() &&
4528 field_type != TypeOracle::GetObjectType()) {
4529 hdr_ << " // Torque type: " << field_type->ToString() << "\n";
4530 }
4531
4532 std::vector<cpp::TemplateParameter> templateParameters = {
4533 cpp::TemplateParameter("D"), cpp::TemplateParameter("P")};
4534 cpp::Class owner(std::move(templateParameters), gen_name_);
4535
4536 // getter
4537 {
4538 auto getter = cpp::Function::DefaultGetter(type_name, &owner, name);
4539 if (indexed) {
4540 getter.AddParameter("int", "i");
4541 }
4542 const char* tag_argument;
4543 switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4544 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4545 tag_argument = "";
4546 break;
4547 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4548 getter.AddParameter("RelaxedLoadTag");
4549 tag_argument = ", kRelaxedLoad";
4550 break;
4551 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4552 getter.AddParameter("AcquireLoadTag");
4553 tag_argument = ", kAcquireLoad";
4554 break;
4555 }
4556
4557 getter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4558
4559 // For tagged data, generate the extra getter that derives an
4560 // PtrComprCageBase from the current object's pointer.
4561 if (can_contain_heap_objects) {
4562 getter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](auto& stream) {
4563 stream
4564 << " PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(*this);\n";
4565 stream << " return " << gen_name_ << "::" << name << "(cage_base"
4566 << (indexed ? ", i" : "") << tag_argument << ");\n";
4567 });
4568
4569 getter.InsertParameter(0, "PtrComprCageBase", "cage_base");
4570 getter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4571 }
4572
4573 getter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](auto& stream) {
4574 EmitLoadFieldStatement(stream, class_field, struct_fields);
4575 stream << " return value;\n";
4576 });
4577 }
4578
4579 // setter
4580 {
4581 auto setter = cpp::Function::DefaultSetter(
4582 &owner, std::string("set_") + name, type_name, "value");
4583 if (indexed) {
4584 setter.InsertParameter(0, "int", "i");
4585 }
4586 switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4587 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4588 break;
4589 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4590 setter.AddParameter("RelaxedStoreTag");
4591 break;
4592 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4593 setter.AddParameter("ReleaseStoreTag");
4594 break;
4595 }
4596 if (can_contain_heap_objects) {
4597 setter.AddParameter("WriteBarrierMode", "mode", "UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER");
4598 }
4599 setter.PrintDeclaration(hdr_);
4600
4601 setter.PrintDefinition(inl_, [&](auto& stream) {
4602 EmitStoreFieldStatement(stream, class_field, struct_fields);
4603 });
4604 }
4605
4606 hdr_ << "\n";
4607}

4609std::string CppClassGenerator::GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(const Field& f) {
4610 if (f.offset.has_value()) {
4611 return "k" + CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset";
4612 }
4613 return CamelifyString(f.name_and_type.name) + "Offset()";
4614}
4615
4616std::string CppClassGenerator::GetTypeNameForAccessor(const Field& f) {
4617 const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
4618 if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
4619 const Type* constexpr_version = field_type->ConstexprVersion();
4620 if (!constexpr_version) {
4621 Error("Field accessor for ", type_->name(), ":: ", f.name_and_type.name,
4622 " cannot be generated because its type ", *field_type,
4623 " is neither a subclass of Object nor does the type have a "
4624 "constexpr "
4625 "version.")
4626 .Position(f.pos)
4627 .Throw();
4628 }
4629 return constexpr_version->GetGeneratedTypeName();
4630 }
4631 return field_type->TagglifiedCppTypeName();
4632}

4634bool CppClassGenerator::CanContainHeapObjects(const Type* t) {
4635 return t->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) &&
4636 !t->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType());

4638
4639void CppClassGenerator::EmitLoadFieldStatement(
4640 std::ostream& stream, const Field& class_field,
4641 std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields) {
4642 const Field& innermost_field =
4643 struct_fields.empty() ? class_field : *struct_fields.back();
4644 const Type* field_type = innermost_field.name_and_type.type;
4645 std::string type_name = GetTypeNameForAccessor(innermost_field);
4646 const std::string class_field_size =
4647 std::get<1>(class_field.GetFieldSizeInformation());
4648
4649 // field_offset contains both the offset from the beginning of the object to
4650 // the class field and the combined offsets of any nested struct fields
4651 // within, but not the index adjustment.
4652 std::string field_offset = GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(class_field);
4653 for (const Field* nested_struct_field : struct_fields) {
4654 field_offset += " + " + std::to_string(*nested_struct_field->offset);
4655 }
4656
4657 std::string offset = field_offset;
4658 if (class_field.index) {
4659 const char* index = class_field.index->optional ? "0" : "i";
4660 GenerateBoundsDCheck(stream, index, type_, class_field);
4661 stream << " int offset = " << field_offset << " + " << index << " * "
4662 << class_field_size << ";\n";
4663 offset = "offset";
4664 }
4665
4666 stream << " " << type_name << " value = ";
4667
4668 if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
4669 const char* load;
4670 switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4671 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4672 load = "ReadField";
4673 break;
4674 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4675 load = "Relaxed_ReadField";
4676 break;
4677 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4678 ReportError("Torque doesn't support @cppAcquireLoad on untagged data");
4679 }
4680 stream << "this->template " << load << "<" << type_name << ">(" << offset
4681 << ");\n";
4682 } else {
4683 const char* load;
4684 switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4685 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4686 load = "load";
4687 break;
4688 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4689 load = "Relaxed_Load";
4690 break;
4691 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4692 load = "Acquire_Load";
4693 break;
4694 }
4695 bool is_smi = field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType());
4696 const std::string load_type = is_smi ? "Smi" : type_name;
4697 const char* postfix = is_smi ? ".value()" : "";
4698 const char* optional_cage_base = is_smi ? "" : "cage_base, ";
4699
4700 stream << "TaggedField<" << load_type << ">::" << load << "("
4701 << optional_cage_base << "*this, " << offset << ")" << postfix
4702 << ";\n";
4703 }
4704
4705 if (CanContainHeapObjects(field_type)) {
4706 stream << " DCHECK(" << GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(field_type, "value")
4707 << ");\n";
4708 }
4709}
4710
4711void CppClassGenerator::EmitStoreFieldStatement(
4712 std::ostream& stream, const Field& class_field,
4713 std::vector<const Field*>& struct_fields) {
4714 const Field& innermost_field =
4715 struct_fields.empty() ? class_field : *struct_fields.back();
4716 const Type* field_type = innermost_field.name_and_type.type;
4717 std::string type_name = GetTypeNameForAccessor(innermost_field);
4718 const std::string class_field_size =
4719 std::get<1>(class_field.GetFieldSizeInformation());
4720
4721 // field_offset contains both the offset from the beginning of the object to
4722 // the class field and the combined offsets of any nested struct fields
4723 // within, but not the index adjustment.
4724 std::string field_offset = GetFieldOffsetForAccessor(class_field);
4725 for (const Field* nested_struct_field : struct_fields) {
4726 field_offset += " + " + std::to_string(*nested_struct_field->offset);
4727 }
4728
4729 std::string offset = field_offset;
4730 if (class_field.index) {
4731 const char* index = class_field.index->optional ? "0" : "i";
4732 GenerateBoundsDCheck(stream, index, type_, class_field);
4733 stream << " int offset = " << field_offset << " + " << index << " * "
4734 << class_field_size << ";\n";
4735 offset = "offset";
4736 }
4737
4738 if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
4739 const char* store;
4740 switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4741 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4742 store = "WriteField";
4743 break;
4744 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4745 store = "Relaxed_WriteField";
4746 break;
4747 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4748 ReportError("Torque doesn't support @cppReleaseStore on untagged data");
4749 }
4750 stream << " this->template " << store << "<" << type_name << ">(" << offset
4751 << ", value);\n";
4752 } else {
4753 bool strong_pointer = field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetObjectType());
4754 bool is_smi = field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType());
4755 const char* write_macro;
4756 if (!strong_pointer) {
4757 if (class_field.synchronization ==
4758 FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease) {
4759 ReportError("Torque doesn't support @cppReleaseStore on weak fields");
4760 }
4761 write_macro = "RELAXED_WRITE_WEAK_FIELD";
4762 } else {
4763 switch (class_field.synchronization) {
4764 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
4765 write_macro = "WRITE_FIELD";
4766 break;
4767 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
4768 write_macro = "RELAXED_WRITE_FIELD";
4769 break;
4770 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
4771 write_macro = "RELEASE_WRITE_FIELD";
4772 break;
4773 }
4774 }
4775 const std::string value_to_write = is_smi ? "Smi::FromInt(value)" : "value";
4776
4777 if (!is_smi) {
4778 // Don't DCHECK types if the roots aren't initialized, so that we don't
4779 // incorrectly fail these checks during initial heap setup.
4780 stream << " "
4781 "SLOW_DCHECK(!IsolateGroup::current()->shared_read_only_heap()-"
4782 ">roots_init_complete() || ("
4783 << GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(field_type, "value") << "));\n";
4784 }
4785 stream << " " << write_macro << "(*this, " << offset << ", "
4786 << value_to_write << ");\n";
4787 if (!is_smi) {
4788 stream << " CONDITIONAL_WRITE_BARRIER(*this, " << offset
4789 << ", value, mode);\n";
4790 }
4791 }
4792}

4797 << "Offsets {\n";

4801 << "Offset = " << *field.offset << ";\n";
4802 }

4804 header << "};\n\n";
4805}

4809void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateClassDefinitions(
4810 const std::string& output_directory) {
4811 std::stringstream factory_header;
4812 std::stringstream factory_impl;
4813 std::string factory_basename = "factory";
4814
4815 std::stringstream forward_declarations;
4816 std::string forward_declarations_filename = "class-forward-declarations.h";
4817
4818 {
4819 factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/factory-base.h\"\n";
4820 factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/factory-base-inl.h\"\n";
4821 factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/heap.h\"\n";
4822 factory_impl << "#include \"src/heap/heap-inl.h\"\n";
4823 factory_impl << "#include \"src/execution/isolate.h\"\n";
4824 factory_impl << "#include "
4825 "\"src/objects/all-objects-inl.h\"\n\n";
4826 NamespaceScope factory_impl_namespaces(factory_impl, {"v8", "internal"});
4827 factory_impl << "\n";
4828
4829 IncludeGuardScope include_guard(forward_declarations,
4830 forward_declarations_filename);
4831 NamespaceScope forward_declarations_namespaces(forward_declarations,
4832 {"v8", "internal"});
4833
4834 std::set<const StructType*, TypeLess> structs_used_in_classes;
4835
4836 // Emit forward declarations.
4837 for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
4838 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(type->GetPosition());
4839 auto& streams = GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(type->AttributedToFile());
4840 std::ostream& header = streams.class_definition_headerfile;
4841 std::string name = type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()
4842 ? type->name()
4843 : type->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName();
4844 if (type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) {
4845 header << "class " << name << ";\n";
4846 }
4847 forward_declarations << "class " << name << ";\n";
4848 }
4849
4850 for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
4851 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(type->GetPosition());
4852 auto& streams = GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(type->AttributedToFile());
4853 std::ostream& header = streams.class_definition_headerfile;
4854 std::ostream& inline_header = streams.class_definition_inline_headerfile;
4855 std::ostream& implementation = streams.class_definition_ccfile;
4856
4857 if (type->ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) {
4858 CppClassGenerator g(type, header, inline_header, implementation);
4859 g.GenerateClass();
4860 } else if (type->ShouldGenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts()) {
4861 CppClassGenerator g(type, header, inline_header, implementation);
4862 g.GenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts();
4863 } else if (type->ShouldGenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts()) {
4864 CppClassGenerator g(type, header, inline_header, implementation);
4865 g.GenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts();
4866 }
4867 for (const Field& f : type->fields()) {
4868 const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
4869 if (auto field_as_struct = field_type->StructSupertype()) {
4870 structs_used_in_classes.insert(*field_as_struct);
4871 }
4872 }
4873 if (type->ShouldGenerateFactoryFunction()) {
4874 std::string return_type =
4875 type->HandlifiedCppTypeName(Type::HandleKind::kIndirect);
4876 std::string function_name = "New" + type->name();
4877 std::stringstream parameters;
4878 for (const Field& f : type->ComputeAllFields()) {
4879 if (f.name_and_type.name == "map") continue;
4880 if (f.name_and_type.name == "self_indirect_pointer") continue;
4881 if (!f.index) {
4882 std::string type_string =
4883 f.name_and_type.type->HandlifiedCppTypeName(
4884 Type::HandleKind::kDirect);
4885 parameters << type_string << " " << f.name_and_type.name << ", ";
4886 }
4887 }
4888 parameters << "AllocationType allocation_type";
4889
4890 factory_header << return_type << " " << function_name << "("
4891 << parameters.str() << ");\n";
4892 factory_impl << "template <typename Impl>\n";
4893 factory_impl << return_type
4894 << " TorqueGeneratedFactory<Impl>::" << function_name
4895 << "(" << parameters.str() << ") {\n";
4896
4897 factory_impl << " int size = ";
4898 const ClassType* super = type->GetSuperClass();
4899 std::string gen_name = "TorqueGenerated" + type->name();
4900 std::string gen_name_T =
4901 gen_name + "<" + type->name() + ", " + super->name() + ">";
4902 factory_impl << gen_name_T << "::SizeFor(";
4903
4904 bool first = true;
4905 auto index_fields = GetOrderedUniqueIndexFields(*type);
4906 CHECK(index_fields.has_value());
4907 for (const auto& index_field : *index_fields) {
4908 if (!first) {
4909 factory_impl << ", ";
4910 }
4911 factory_impl << index_field.name_and_type.name;
4912 first = false;
4913 }
4914
4915 factory_impl << ");\n";
4916 factory_impl << " Tagged<Map> map = factory()->read_only_roots()."
4917 << SnakeifyString(type->name()) << "_map();\n";
4918 factory_impl << " Tagged<HeapObject> raw_object =\n";
4919 factory_impl << " factory()->AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(size, "
4920 "allocation_type, map);\n";
4921 factory_impl << " " << type->TagglifiedCppTypeName()
4922 << " result = Cast<"
4923 << type->GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName()
4924 << ">(raw_object);\n";
4925 factory_impl << " DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;\n";
4926 factory_impl << " WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode =\n"
4927 << " allocation_type == AllocationType::kYoung\n"
4928 << " ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;\n"
4929 << " USE(write_barrier_mode);\n";
4930
4931 for (const Field& f : type->ComputeAllFields()) {
4932 if (f.name_and_type.name == "map") continue;
4933 if (f.name_and_type.name == "self_indirect_pointer") {
4934 factory_impl << " "
4935 "result->init_self_indirect_pointer(factory()->"
4936 "isolate());\n";
4937 } else if (!f.index) {
4938 factory_impl << " result->TorqueGeneratedClass::set_"
4939 << SnakeifyString(f.name_and_type.name) << "(";
4940 if (f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(
4941 TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) &&
4942 !f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType())) {
4943 factory_impl << "*" << f.name_and_type.name
4944 << ", write_barrier_mode";
4945 } else {
4946 factory_impl << f.name_and_type.name;
4947 }
4948 factory_impl << ");\n";
4949 }
4950 }
4951
4952 factory_impl << " return handle(result, factory()->isolate());\n";
4953 factory_impl << "}\n\n";
4954
4955 factory_impl << "template EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DEFINE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE) "
4956 << return_type
4957 << " TorqueGeneratedFactory<Factory>::" << function_name
4958 << "(" << parameters.str() << ");\n";
4959 factory_impl << "template EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DEFINE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE) "
4960 << return_type << " TorqueGeneratedFactory<LocalFactory>::"
4961 << function_name << "(" << parameters.str() << ");\n";
4962
4963 factory_impl << "\n\n";
4964 }
4965 }
4966
4967 for (const StructType* type : structs_used_in_classes) {
4968 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(type->GetPosition());
4969 std::ostream& header =
4970 GlobalContext::GeneratedPerFile(type->GetPosition().source)
4971 .class_definition_headerfile;
4972 if (type != TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrHoleType()) {
4973 GenerateStructLayoutDescription(header, type);
4974 }
4975 }
4976 }
4977 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + factory_basename + ".inc",
4978 factory_header.str());
4979 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + factory_basename + ".cc",
4980 factory_impl.str());
4981 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + forward_declarations_filename,
4982 forward_declarations.str());
4983}

4986void GeneratePrintDefinitionsForClass(std::ostream& impl, const ClassType* type,
4987 const std::string& gen_name,
4988 const std::string& gen_name_T,
4989 const std::string template_params) {
4990 impl << template_params << "\n";
4991 impl << "void " << gen_name_T << "::" << type->name()
4992 << "Print(std::ostream& os) {\n";
4993 impl << " this->PrintHeader(os, \"" << type->name() << "\");\n";
4994 auto hierarchy = type->GetHierarchy();
4995 std::map<std::string, const AggregateType*> field_names;
4996 for (const AggregateType* aggregate_type : hierarchy) {
4997 for (const Field& f : aggregate_type->fields()) {
4998 if (f.name_and_type.name == "map" || f.index.has_value() ||
4999 !CanGenerateFieldAccessors(f.name_and_type.type)) {
5000 continue;
5001 }
5002 std::string getter = f.name_and_type.name;
5003 if (aggregate_type != type) {
5004 // We must call getters directly on the class that provided them,
5005 // because a subclass could have hidden them.
5006 getter = aggregate_type->name() + "::TorqueGeneratedClass::" + getter;
5007 }
5008 if (f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType()) ||
5009 !f.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
5010 impl << " os << \"\\n - " << f.name_and_type.name << ": \" << ";
5011 if (f.name_and_type.type->StructSupertype()) {
5012 // TODO(turbofan): Print struct fields too.
5013 impl << "\" <struct field printing still unimplemented>\";\n";
5014 } else {
5015 impl << "this->" << getter;
5016 switch (f.synchronization) {
5017 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
5018 impl << "();\n";
5019 break;
5020 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
5021 impl << "(kRelaxedLoad);\n";
5022 break;
5023 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
5024 impl << "(kAcquireLoad);\n";
5025 break;
5026 }
5027 }
5028 } else {
5029 impl << " os << \"\\n - " << f.name_and_type.name << ": \" << "
5030 << "Brief(this->" << getter;
5031 switch (f.synchronization) {
5032 case FieldSynchronization::kNone:
5033 impl << "());\n";
5034 break;
5035 case FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed:
5036 impl << "(kRelaxedLoad));\n";
5037 break;
5038 case FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease:
5039 impl << "(kAcquireLoad));\n";
5040 break;
5041 }
5042 }
5043 }
5044 }
5045 impl << " os << '\\n';\n";
5046 impl << "}\n\n";
5047}

5078
5079std::optional<std::string> MatchSimpleBodyDescriptor(const ClassType* type) {
5080 std::vector<ObjectSlotKind> slots = type->ComputeHeaderSlotKinds();
5081 if (!type->HasStaticSize()) {
5082 slots.push_back(*type->ComputeArraySlotKind());
5083 }
5084
5085 // Skip the map slot.
5086 size_t i = 1;
5087 while (i < slots.size() && slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer) ++i;
5088 if (i == slots.size()) return "DataOnlyBodyDescriptor";
5089 bool has_weak_pointers = false;
5090 size_t start_index = i;
5091 for (; i < slots.size(); ++i) {
5092 if (slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kStrongPointer) {
5093 continue;
5094 } else if (slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kMaybeObjectPointer) {
5095 has_weak_pointers = true;
5096 } else if (slots[i] == ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer) {
5097 break;
5098 } else {
5099 return std::nullopt;
5100 }
5101 }
5102 size_t end_index = i;
5103 for (; i < slots.size(); ++i) {
5104 if (slots[i] != ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer) return std::nullopt;
5105 }
5106 size_t start_offset = start_index * TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5107 size_t end_offset = end_index * TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5108 // We pick a suffix-range body descriptor even in cases where the object size
5109 // is fixed, to reduce the amount of code executed for object visitation.
5110 if (end_index == slots.size()) {
5111 return ToString("SuffixRange", has_weak_pointers ? "Weak" : "",
5112 "BodyDescriptor<", start_offset, ">");
5113 }
5114 if (!has_weak_pointers) {
5115 return ToString("FixedRangeBodyDescriptor<", start_offset, ", ", end_offset,
5116 ">");
5117 }
5118 return std::nullopt;
5119}
5120
5121void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateBodyDescriptors(
5122 const std::string& output_directory) {
5123 std::string file_name = "objects-body-descriptors-inl.inc";
5124 std::stringstream h_contents;
5125
5126 for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5127 std::string name = type->name();
5128 if (!type->ShouldGenerateBodyDescriptor()) continue;
5129
5130 bool has_array_fields = !type->HasStaticSize();
5131 std::vector<ObjectSlotKind> header_slot_kinds =
5132 type->ComputeHeaderSlotKinds();
5133 std::optional<ObjectSlotKind> array_slot_kind =
5134 type->ComputeArraySlotKind();
5135 DCHECK_EQ(has_array_fields, array_slot_kind.has_value());
5136
5137 h_contents << "class " << name << "::BodyDescriptor final : public ";
5138 if (auto descriptor_name = MatchSimpleBodyDescriptor(type)) {
5139 h_contents << *descriptor_name << " {\n";
5140 h_contents << " public:\n";
5141 } else {
5142 h_contents << "BodyDescriptorBase {\n";
5143 h_contents << " public:\n";
5144
5145 h_contents << " template <typename ObjectVisitor>\n";
5146 h_contents
5147 << " static inline void IterateBody(Tagged<Map> map, "
5148 "Tagged<HeapObject> obj, int object_size, ObjectVisitor* v) {\n";
5149
5150 std::vector<ObjectSlotKind> slots = std::move(header_slot_kinds);
5151 if (has_array_fields) slots.push_back(*array_slot_kind);
5152
5153 // Skip the map slot.
5154 slots.erase(slots.begin());
5155 size_t start_offset = TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5156
5157 size_t end_offset = start_offset;
5158 ObjectSlotKind section_kind;
5159 for (size_t i = 0; i <= slots.size(); ++i) {
5160 std::optional<ObjectSlotKind> next_section_kind;
5161 bool finished_section = false;
5162 if (i == 0) {
5163 next_section_kind = slots[i];
5164 } else if (i < slots.size()) {
5165 if (auto combined = Combine(section_kind, slots[i])) {
5166 next_section_kind = *combined;
5167 } else {
5168 next_section_kind = slots[i];
5169 finished_section = true;
5170 }
5171 } else {
5172 finished_section = true;
5173 }
5174 if (finished_section) {
5175 bool is_array_slot = i == slots.size() && has_array_fields;
5176 bool multiple_slots =
5177 is_array_slot ||
5178 (end_offset - start_offset > TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize());
5179 std::optional<std::string> iterate_command;
5180 switch (section_kind) {
5181 case ObjectSlotKind::kStrongPointer:
5182 iterate_command = "IteratePointer";
5183 break;
5184 case ObjectSlotKind::kMaybeObjectPointer:
5185 iterate_command = "IterateMaybeWeakPointer";
5186 break;
5187 case ObjectSlotKind::kCustomWeakPointer:
5188 iterate_command = "IterateCustomWeakPointer";
5189 break;
5190 case ObjectSlotKind::kNoPointer:
5191 break;
5192 }
5193 if (iterate_command) {
5194 if (multiple_slots) *iterate_command += "s";
5195 h_contents << " " << *iterate_command << "(obj, "
5196 << start_offset;
5197 if (multiple_slots) {
5198 h_contents << ", "
5199 << (i == slots.size() ? "object_size"
5200 : std::to_string(end_offset));
5201 }
5202 h_contents << ", v);\n";
5203 }
5204 start_offset = end_offset;
5205 }
5206 if (i < slots.size()) section_kind = *next_section_kind;
5207 end_offset += TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize();
5208 }
5209
5210 h_contents << " }\n\n";
5211 }
5212
5213 h_contents << " static inline int SizeOf(Tagged<Map> map, "
5214 "Tagged<HeapObject> raw_object) {\n";
5215 if (type->size().SingleValue()) {
5216 h_contents << " return " << *type->size().SingleValue() << ";\n";
5217 } else {
5218 // We use an UncheckedCast here because this is used for concurrent
5219 // marking, where we shouldn't re-read the map.
5220 h_contents << " return UncheckedCast<" << name
5221 << ">(raw_object)->AllocatedSize();\n";
5222 }
5223 h_contents << " }\n\n";
5224
5225 h_contents << "};\n";
5226 }
5227
5228 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name, h_contents.str());
5229}

5233// Generate verification code for a single piece of class data, which might be
5234// nested within a struct or might be a single element in an indexed field (or
5235// both).
5236void GenerateFieldValueVerifier(const std::string& class_name, bool indexed,
5237 std::string offset, const Field& leaf_field,
5238 std::string indexed_field_size,
5239 std::ostream& cc_contents, bool is_map) {
5240 const Type* field_type = leaf_field.name_and_type.type;
5241
5242 bool maybe_object =
5243 !field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetStrongTaggedType());
5244 const char* object_type = maybe_object ? "MaybeObject" : "Object";
5245 const char* tagged_object_type =
5246 maybe_object ? "Tagged<MaybeObject>" : "Tagged<Object>";
5247 const char* verify_fn =
5248 maybe_object ? "VerifyMaybeObjectPointer" : "VerifyPointer";
5249 if (indexed) {
5250 offset += " + i * " + indexed_field_size;
5251 }
5252 // Name the local var based on the field name for nicer CHECK output.
5253 const std::string value = leaf_field.name_and_type.name + "__value";
5254
5255 // Read the field.
5256 if (is_map) {
5257 cc_contents << " " << tagged_object_type << " " << value
5258 << " = o->map();\n";
5259 } else {
5260 cc_contents << " " << tagged_object_type << " " << value
5261 << " = TaggedField<" << object_type << ">::load(o, " << offset
5262 << ");\n";
5263 }
5264
5265 // Call VerifyPointer or VerifyMaybeObjectPointer on it.
5266 cc_contents << " Object::" << verify_fn << "(isolate, " << value << ");\n";
5267
5268 // Check that the value is of an appropriate type. We can skip this part for
5269 // the Object type because it would not check anything beyond what we already
5270 // checked with VerifyPointer.
5271 if (field_type != TypeOracle::GetObjectType()) {
5272 cc_contents << " CHECK(" << GenerateRuntimeTypeCheck(field_type, value)
5273 << ");\n";
5274 }
5275}
5276
5277void GenerateClassFieldVerifier(const std::string& class_name,
5278 const ClassType& class_type, const Field& f,
5279 std::ostream& h_contents,
5280 std::ostream& cc_contents) {
5281 const Type* field_type = f.name_and_type.type;
5282
5283 // We only verify tagged types, not raw numbers or pointers. Structs
5284 // consisting of tagged types are also included.
5285 if (!field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType()) &&
5286 !field_type->StructSupertype())
5287 return;
5288 // Protected pointer fields cannot be read or verified from torque yet.
5289 if (field_type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetProtectedPointerType())) return;
5290 if (field_type == TypeOracle::GetFloat64OrHoleType()) return;
5291 // Do not verify if the field may be uninitialized.
5292 if (TypeOracle::GetUninitializedType()->IsSubtypeOf(field_type)) return;
5293
5294 std::string field_start_offset;
5295 if (f.index) {
5296 field_start_offset = f.name_and_type.name + "__offset";
5297 std::string length = f.name_and_type.name + "__length";
5298 cc_contents << " intptr_t " << field_start_offset << ", " << length
5299 << ";\n";
5300 cc_contents << " std::tie(std::ignore, " << field_start_offset << ", "
5301 << length << ") = "
5302 << Callable::PrefixNameForCCOutput(
5303 class_type.GetSliceMacroName(f))
5304 << "(o);\n";
5305
5306 // Slices use intptr, but TaggedField<T>.load() uses int, so verify that
5307 // such a cast is valid.
5308 cc_contents << " CHECK_EQ(" << field_start_offset << ", static_cast<int>("
5309 << field_start_offset << "));\n";
5310 cc_contents << " CHECK_EQ(" << length << ", static_cast<int>(" << length
5311 << "));\n";
5312 field_start_offset = "static_cast<int>(" + field_start_offset + ")";
5313 length = "static_cast<int>(" + length + ")";
5314
5315 cc_contents << " for (int i = 0; i < " << length << "; ++i) {\n";
5316 } else {
5317 // Non-indexed fields have known offsets.
5318 field_start_offset = std::to_string(*f.offset);
5319 cc_contents << " {\n";
5320 }
5321
5322 if (auto struct_type = field_type->StructSupertype()) {
5323 for (const Field& struct_field : (*struct_type)->fields()) {
5324 if (struct_field.name_and_type.type->IsSubtypeOf(
5325 TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
5326 GenerateFieldValueVerifier(
5327 class_name, f.index.has_value(),
5328 field_start_offset + " + " + std::to_string(*struct_field.offset),
5329 struct_field, std::to_string((*struct_type)->PackedSize()),
5330 cc_contents, f.name_and_type.name == "map");
5331 }
5332 }
5333 } else {
5334 GenerateFieldValueVerifier(class_name, f.index.has_value(),
5335 field_start_offset, f, "kTaggedSize",
5336 cc_contents, f.name_and_type.name == "map");
5337 }
5338
5339 cc_contents << " }\n";
5340}

5344void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateClassVerifiers(
5345 const std::string& output_directory) {
5346 std::string file_name = "class-verifiers";
5347 std::stringstream h_contents;
5348 std::stringstream cc_contents;
5349 {
5350 IncludeGuardScope include_guard(h_contents, file_name + ".h");
5351 IfDefScope verify_heap_h(h_contents, "VERIFY_HEAP");
5352 IfDefScope verify_heap_cc(cc_contents, "VERIFY_HEAP");
5353
5354 h_contents << "#include \"src/base/macros.h\"\n\n";
5355
5356 cc_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/" << file_name << ".h\"\n\n";
5357 cc_contents << "#include \"src/objects/all-objects-inl.h\"\n";
5358
5359 IncludeObjectMacrosScope object_macros(cc_contents);
5360
5361 NamespaceScope h_namespaces(h_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5362 NamespaceScope cc_namespaces(cc_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5363
5364 cc_contents
5365 << "#include \"torque-generated/test/torque/test-torque-tq-inl.inc\"\n";
5366
5367 // Generate forward declarations to avoid including any headers.
5368 h_contents << "class Isolate;\n";
5369 h_contents << "template<typename T>\nclass Tagged;\n";
5370 for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5371 if (!type->ShouldGenerateVerify()) continue;
5372 h_contents << "class " << type->name() << ";\n";
5373 }
5374
5375 const char* verifier_class = "TorqueGeneratedClassVerifiers";
5376
5377 h_contents << "class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE " << verifier_class << "{\n";
5378 h_contents << " public:\n";
5379
5380 for (const ClassType* type : TypeOracle::GetClasses()) {
5381 std::string name = type->name();
5382 std::string cpp_name = type->TagglifiedCppTypeName();
5383 if (!type->ShouldGenerateVerify()) continue;
5384
5385 std::string method_name = name + "Verify";
5386
5387 h_contents << " static void " << method_name << "(" << cpp_name
5388 << " o, Isolate* isolate);\n";
5389
5390 cc_contents << "void " << verifier_class << "::" << method_name << "("
5391 << cpp_name << " o, Isolate* isolate) {\n";
5392
5393 // First, do any verification for the super class. Not all classes have
5394 // verifiers, so skip to the nearest super class that has one.
5395 const ClassType* super_type = type->GetSuperClass();
5396 while (super_type && !super_type->ShouldGenerateVerify()) {
5397 super_type = super_type->GetSuperClass();
5398 }
5399 if (super_type) {
5400 std::string super_name = super_type->name();
5401 cc_contents << " o->" << super_name << "Verify(isolate);\n";
5402 }
5403
5404 // Second, verify that this object is what it claims to be.
5405 cc_contents << " CHECK(Is" << name << "(o, isolate));\n";
5406
5407 // Third, verify its properties.
5408 for (const auto& f : type->fields()) {
5409 GenerateClassFieldVerifier(name, *type, f, h_contents, cc_contents);
5410 }
5411
5412 cc_contents << "}\n";
5413 }
5414
5415 h_contents << "};\n";
5416 }
5417 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".h", h_contents.str());
5418 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".cc", cc_contents.str());
5419}

5421void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateEnumVerifiers(
5422 const std::string& output_directory) {
5423 std::string file_name = "enum-verifiers";
5424 std::stringstream cc_contents;
5425 {
5426 cc_contents << "#include \"src/compiler/code-assembler.h\"\n";
5427 for (const std::string& include_path : GlobalContext::CppIncludes()) {
5428 cc_contents << "#include " << StringLiteralQuote(include_path) << "\n";
5429 }
5430 cc_contents << "\n";
5431
5432 NamespaceScope cc_namespaces(cc_contents, {"v8", "internal", ""});
5433
5434 cc_contents << "class EnumVerifier {\n";
5435 for (const auto& desc : GlobalContext::Get().ast()->EnumDescriptions()) {
5436 std::stringstream alias_checks;
5437 cc_contents << " // " << desc.name << " (" << desc.pos << ")\n";
5438 cc_contents << " void VerifyEnum_" << desc.name << "("
5439 << desc.constexpr_generates
5440 << " x) {\n"
5441 " switch(x) {\n";
5442 for (const auto& entry : desc.entries) {
5443 if (entry.alias_entry.empty()) {
5444 cc_contents << " case " << entry.name << ": break;\n";
5445 } else {
5446 // We don't add a case for this, because it aliases another entry, so
5447 // we would have two cases for the same value.
5448 alias_checks << " static_assert(" << entry.name
5449 << " == " << entry.alias_entry << ");\n";
5450 }
5451 }
5452 if (desc.is_open) cc_contents << " default: break;\n";
5453 cc_contents << " }\n";
5454 cc_contents << alias_checks.str();
5455 cc_contents << " }\n\n";
5456 }
5457 cc_contents << "};\n";
5458 }
5459
5460 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".cc", cc_contents.str());
5461}

5463void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateExportedMacrosAssembler(
5464 const std::string& output_directory) {
5465 std::string file_name = "exported-macros-assembler";
5466 std::stringstream h_contents;
5467 std::stringstream cc_contents;
5468 {
5469 IncludeGuardScope include_guard(h_contents, file_name + ".h");
5470
5471 h_contents << "#include \"src/compiler/code-assembler.h\"\n";
5472 h_contents << "#include \"src/execution/frames.h\"\n";
5473 h_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/csa-types.h\"\n";
5474
5475 for (const std::string& include_path : GlobalContext::CppIncludes()) {
5476 cc_contents << "#include " << StringLiteralQuote(include_path) << "\n";
5477 }
5478 cc_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/" << file_name << ".h\"\n";
5479
5480 for (SourceId file : SourceFileMap::AllSources()) {
5481 cc_contents << "#include \"torque-generated/" +
5482 SourceFileMap::PathFromV8RootWithoutExtension(file) +
5483 "-tq-csa.h\"\n";
5484 }
5485
5486 NamespaceScope h_namespaces(h_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5487 NamespaceScope cc_namespaces(cc_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5488
5489 h_contents << "class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE "
5490 "TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler {\n"
5491 << " public:\n"
5492 << " explicit TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler"
5493 "(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state) : state_(state) {\n"
5494 << " USE(state_);\n"
5495 << " }\n";
5496
5497 for (auto& declarable : GlobalContext::AllDeclarables()) {
5498 TorqueMacro* macro = TorqueMacro::DynamicCast(declarable.get());
5499 if (!(macro && macro->IsExportedToCSA())) continue;
5500 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(macro->Position());
5501
5502 cpp::Class assembler("TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler");
5503 std::vector<std::string> generated_parameter_names;
5504 cpp::Function f = GenerateFunction(
5505 &assembler, macro->ReadableName(), macro->signature(),
5506 macro->parameter_names(), false, &generated_parameter_names);
5507
5508 f.PrintDeclaration(h_contents);
5509 f.PrintDefinition(cc_contents, [&](std::ostream& stream) {
5510 stream << "return " << macro->ExternalName() << "(state_";
5511 for (const auto& name : generated_parameter_names) {
5512 stream << ", " << name;
5513 }
5514 stream << ");";
5515 });
5516 }
5517
5518 h_contents << " private:\n"
5519 << " compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state_;\n"
5520 << "};\n";
5521 }
5522 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".h", h_contents.str());
5523 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".cc", cc_contents.str());
5524}

5528void CollectAllFields(const std::string& path, const Field& field,
5529 std::vector<std::string>& result) {
5530 if (field.name_and_type.type->StructSupertype()) {
5531 std::string next_path = path + field.name_and_type.name + ".";
5532 const StructType* struct_type =
5533 StructType::DynamicCast(field.name_and_type.type);
5534 for (const auto& inner_field : struct_type->fields()) {
5535 CollectAllFields(next_path, inner_field, result);
5536 }
5537 } else {
5538 result.push_back(path + field.name_and_type.name);
5539 }
5540}

5543
5544void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateCSATypes(
5545 const std::string& output_directory) {
5546 std::string file_name = "csa-types";
5547 std::stringstream h_contents;
5548 {
5549 IncludeGuardScope include_guard(h_contents, file_name + ".h");
5550 h_contents << "#include \"src/compiler/code-assembler.h\"\n\n";
5551
5552 NamespaceScope h_namespaces(h_contents, {"v8", "internal"});
5553
5554 // Generates headers for all structs in a topologically-sorted order, since
5555 // TypeOracle keeps them in the order of their resolution
5556 for (const auto& type : TypeOracle::GetAggregateTypes()) {
5557 const StructType* struct_type = StructType::DynamicCast(type.get());
5558 if (!struct_type) continue;
5559 h_contents << "struct " << struct_type->GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl()
5560 << " {\n";
5561 for (auto& field : struct_type->fields()) {
5562 h_contents << " " << field.name_and_type.type->GetGeneratedTypeName();
5563 h_contents << " " << field.name_and_type.name << ";\n";
5564 }
5565 h_contents << "\n std::tuple<";
5566 bool first = true;
5567 for (const Type* lowered_type : LowerType(struct_type)) {
5568 if (!first) {
5569 h_contents << ", ";
5570 }
5571 first = false;
5572 h_contents << lowered_type->GetGeneratedTypeName();
5573 }
5574 std::vector<std::string> all_fields;
5575 for (auto& field : struct_type->fields()) {
5576 CollectAllFields("", field, all_fields);
5577 }
5578 h_contents << "> Flatten() const {\n"
5579 " return std::make_tuple(";
5580 PrintCommaSeparatedList(h_contents, all_fields);
5581 h_contents << ");\n";
5582 h_contents << " }\n";
5583 h_contents << "};\n";
5584 }
5585 }
5586 WriteFile(output_directory + "/" + file_name + ".h", h_contents.str());
5587}
5588
5589void ReportAllUnusedMacros() {
5590 for (const auto& declarable : GlobalContext::AllDeclarables()) {
5591 if (!declarable->IsMacro() || declarable->IsExternMacro()) continue;
5592
5593 Macro* macro = Macro::cast(declarable.get());
5594 if (macro->IsUsed()) continue;
5595
5596 if (macro->IsTorqueMacro() && TorqueMacro::cast(macro)->IsExportedToCSA()) {
5597 continue;
5598 }
5599 // TODO(gsps): Mark methods of generic structs used if they are used in any
5600 // instantiation
5601 if (Method* method = Method::DynamicCast(macro)) {
5602 if (StructType* struct_type =
5603 StructType::DynamicCast(method->aggregate_type())) {
5604 if (struct_type->GetSpecializedFrom().has_value()) {
5605 continue;
5606 }
5607 }
5608 }
5609
5610 std::vector<std::string> ignored_prefixes = {"Convert<", "Cast<",
5611 "FromConstexpr<"};
5612 const std::string name = macro->ReadableName();
5613 const bool ignore =
5614 StartsWithSingleUnderscore(name) ||
5615 std::any_of(ignored_prefixes.begin(), ignored_prefixes.end(),
5616 [&name](const std::string& prefix) {
5617 return StringStartsWith(name, prefix);
5618 });
5619
5620 if (!ignore) {
5621 Lint("Macro '", macro->ReadableName(), "' is never used.")
5622 .Position(macro->IdentifierPosition());
5623 }
5624 }
5625}
